(1, 'Martial Arts Is the #1 Best Sport for Children', '<h3>My top ten powerful reasons why</h3><p>Author Photo — Some of our students. Five of them are teen black belts and still training today. /used with permission</p><p>If you have children, you’ve most likely thought of getting them into some kind of physical activity. You know how important it is to exercise. And you know that school does not always give them the best social engagement.</p><p>So…</p><p>I want to convince you that the ideal sport to get your child into is Martial Arts.</p><h3>Before I give you my reasons,</h3><p>I want you to know that this belief is based on my life experience including, but not limited to, the following:</p><p><strong>I was a child athlete</strong> — playing multiple sports competitively from age 7–17.</p><p><strong>I was an uncomfortable teen girl</strong> — searching, dangerously, for validation.</p><p><strong>I was a young adult trying to find my place in life</strong> — this is when I began my martial arts journey.</p><p><strong>I was a school teacher </strong>— teaching special education for 10 years.</p><p><strong>I was/am a mom of three </strong>— who are now amazing, young adult black belts.</p><p><strong>I was/am a devout martial artist</strong> — now with 30 years of experience in the Korean styles of taekwondo and hapkido.</p><p><strong>I was/am a studio owner and master instructor </strong>— and have worked with a few thousand children and their families.</p><p>So now, at age 55, I will share 10 reasons I believe the martial arts stand out from other sports. And why there are few things better that you can do for your child than support them in earning their black belt.<figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:533,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/0*HYaOIYlSMZSPv9Ay&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:800}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Photo by Timo Müller on Unsplash&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/0*HYaOIYlSMZSPv9Ay\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited\">Photo by Timo Müller on Unsplash</figcaption></figure>I will start with number ten and work my way up to my number one favorite reason.</p><p><strong>#10 — Martial arts is a whole-body workout; making it great on its own, or as cross-training.</strong></p><p>It helps with body awareness and coordination in general, and it teaches skills that will help in any sport should your child decide to pursue one down the road. This makes it a great first physical activity for young children. For older children and adults, it will improve coordination, strength, and reaction time, which will carry over into your other physical activities.</p><p><strong>#9 — In martial arts, everyone gets to play.</strong></p><p>There are no bench warmers. This is probably the biggest issue people have with team sports. Many kids don’t even get to play, yet they may put just as much time and effort into their practices. I do understand that is just the way it is, and such is life. But that also makes it one of the reasons I love martial arts. No bench warmers.</p><p><strong>#8 — Martial arts is both an individual AND a team sport.</strong></p><p>If you like working alone, this is for you. If you like being part of a group, this is for you. You are working both together and alone at the same time. You do not have to worry about “bringing the team down,” so to speak, but at the same time, you can reap the benefits of being encouraged by the group. If you want more of a team feel, some studios have sparring and/or demonstration teams that train even harder together.</p><p><strong>#7 — Martial arts can be competitive…or not.</strong></p><p>The only person you are competing with is yourself. You want to try to always be better than you were, but it does not matter how you compare to the other students in class. You move up when you are ready. However, there ARE opportunities to do competitions if you want to. Taekwondo tournaments allow students to test their skills against others, but it is usually not required.</p><p><strong>#6 — In martial arts, everyone can become a star.</strong></p><p>Why? Because ALL students will become a black belt if they do not give up. It is hard work, but you are guaranteed the accolades and the feeling of awesomeness IF you put in the time and effort. And isn’t that what we want to teach our kids about life?<figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:533,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/0*g15PUmGfoRYOCNzP&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:800}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Photo by Leslie Jones on Unsplash&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/0*g15PUmGfoRYOCNzP\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited\">Photo by Leslie Jones on Unsplash</figcaption></figure><strong>#5 — As a martial arts student, you will be part of a positive, life-affirming, community.</strong></p><p>Being part of a positive community is so important. Life can be tough, so it is nice to have a place to go where everyone has a similar goal and supports each other. School can be hard on many kids socially. The studio is a place they can go and not worry about social groups. Mutual respect is expected.</p><p><strong>#4 — On your martial arts journey, you are learning how to defend yourself, a practical life skill, while doing the sport.</strong></p><p>How cool is that?! Not only are you getting great exercise, but you are also learning how to protect yourself at the same time. So as you train, you are becoming less likely to ever be a target of bullying or violence.</p><p><strong>#3 — In martial arts, boys and girls play together, get strong together, and gain mutual respect for one another.</strong></p><p>This is so awesome that I toyed with making it number one on my list. Boys and girls train side by side and even spar with one another. They also hang out together at events, help each other learn skills, and break the same boards and bricks. They earn the same black belt together. I truly believe if everyone did martial arts, there would be much fewer incidences of sexual assault. A feeling of equality is the key here.</p><p><strong>#2 — Building character is inherent in martial arts.</strong></p><p>Yes, being part of any sport can build character. However, in martial arts, it is the PURPOSE, so students are specifically taught things to build positive character traits. There are so many positive traits, in fact, that I will do separate articles on the character benefits of martial arts.</p><p><strong>#1 — Above all, the goal of martial arts is to build true confidence.</strong></p><p>As parents, we want our children to be confident as they walk through life. Confident kids don’t get picked on, and they don’t pick on others. They are also kinder and more likely to stand up for others. But confidence is difficult for kids to achieve when there is so much pressure on them to be good at everything. That’s why I LOVE that building confidence is the ESSENCE of martial arts. I do believe, it is the number one most important trait we should strive to instill in our children as they grow up.</p><p>Now that is quite a list and quite a claim I am making. But I am adamant that parents should get their kids into martial arts. Yes, it is dependent on finding a good, reputable studio. Fortunately, most masters teach because they want to make a difference, so there are many good ones out there.</p><p>What are you waiting for!!!</p><p>Oh, you’re not sure where to go? I promise to write a piece soon on “How to Find a Martial Arts Studio That Is Right for You.”</p><p><em>I am a martial arts master. My training and teaching over these past 30 years have given me much insight. And I want to share it with others in any way I can. It is my sincere desire to help you feel safe, strong, and able to defend yourself, both physically and mentally, as you walk through life.</em></p><p><em>Sending you strength, love, and wisdom! — Jodi</em></p><p><br></p>', '01JGDR2QAREK7D0WP6RSRZAWEN.png', 'featured', 0, 2, 'martial-arts-is-the-1-best-sport-for-children', '2025-11-11 18:29:50', '2024-12-30 22:57:30', '2025-11-11 18:29:50'),
(2, 'Desa Karang Bunga Masuk Tahapan Penilaian Provinsi', '<p><figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image/webp&quot;,&quot;filename&quot;:&quot;IMG_20180419_201205.jpg.webp&quot;,&quot;filesize&quot;:146678,&quot;height&quot;:800,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;http://magayazid.test//storage/QpNLcdFBvFYrfCR6jjV590Ov3YbmFVLVKKC5xR28.webp&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;http://magayazid.test//storage/QpNLcdFBvFYrfCR6jjV590Ov3YbmFVLVKKC5xR28.webp&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:1200}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image/webp\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;presentation&quot;:&quot;gallery&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview attachment--webp\"><a href=\"http://magayazid.test//storage/QpNLcdFBvFYrfCR6jjV590Ov3YbmFVLVKKC5xR28.webp\"><img src=\"http://magayazid.test//storage/QpNLcdFBvFYrfCR6jjV590Ov3YbmFVLVKKC5xR28.webp\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption\"><span class=\"attachment__name\">IMG_20180419_201205.jpg.webp</span> <span class=\"attachment__size\">143.24 KB</span></figcaption></a></figure></p><p>Marabahan, (Antaranews Kalsel) - Desa Karang Bunga, Kecamatan Mandastana, Kabupaten Barito Kuala, Kalimantan Selatan, mendapat kunjungan dari Tim Lomba Desa Tingkat Provinsi Kalsel, Kamis (19/4).</p><p><br>Tim terdiri dari beberapa unsur tersebut diterima Bupati Batola Hj Noormiliyani AS, Forkopimda, Ketua TP-PKK Hj Saraswati Dwi Putranti beserta pengurus baik kabupaten , kecamatan dan desa, para pejabat eselon II, III, dan berbagai lapisan masyarakat.</p><p>Sekretaris DPMD Provinsi Kalsel M Helfianoor mewakili Gubernur Kalsel H Sahbirin Noor mengatakan, kehadiran tim dalam rangka melakukan penilaian dan evaluasi, mengingat Desa Karang Bunga terpilih mewaliki Batola pada Lomba Desa Tingkat Provinsi Kalsel 2018.</p><p>Menurut dia, berbagai aspek yang dinilai selain kegiatan, administrasi, dan inovasi desa juga dinilai menyangkut keunggulan desa.</p><p>Diutarakannya, lomba desa dan kelurahan pada hakekatnya salah satu alat perekat kerukunan masyarakat melalui partisipasi, kerjasama dan kemandirian masyarakat dalam membangun desa dan kelurahan.</p><p>Kegiatan tersebut, sebutnya, dapat dijadikan indikator sejauh mana perkembangan kemajuan pembangunan selama kurun waktu satu tahun baik di bidang pemerintahan, pembangunan dan kemasyarakatan.</p><p>Dengan demikian, jelas dia, masyarakat akan dapat lebih terpacu untuk berperan secara aktif demi terciptanya kemandirian masyarakat dalam membangun wilayahnya.</p><p>Sehingga, ungkap dia, menjadikan pembangunan desa dan kelurahan bisa dilakukan secara terpadu dan menyeluruh baik pembangunan fisik maupun pembangunan masyarakat dan pemerintahan.</p><p>Tepisah, Bupati Batola Hj Noormiliyani menilai, perlombaan desa dan kelurahan ini sangat bermanfaat bagi masyarakat di daerah.</p><p>Mengingat dari kegiatan yang diselenggarakan itu, ucap dia, dapat membangun kemandirian desa dan kelurahan dalam rangka mendukung upaya percepatan kemajuan pembangunan sekarang ini lebih dititikberatkan pada pencapaian kemajuan pembangunan di perdesaan.</p><p>Mantan Ketua DPRD Provinsi Kalsel berharap, melalui kegiatan tersebut semakin memotivasi aparatur pemerintahan desa bersama-sama dengan warganya untuk lebih meningkatkan peran dan partisipasi aktifnya dalam mengelola dan membangun desanya.</p><p>“Diharapkan mampu meningkatkan kemajuan pembangunan dan kesejahteraan hidup warga desa diwilayahnya sesuai dengan Visi Pembangunan Batola Setara tahun 2017-2022,” ungkapnya.</p><p>Menariknya, sebelum penilaian dilaksanakan, tim terlebih dahulu mendapat suguhan tarian penyambutan Radap Rahayu dari Sanggar Seni Karang Bunga, tarian siswa siswi TK Darussalam, penampilan siswa siswi PAUD KB Kencana dan menampilkan paduan suara Mars PKK dari ibu-ibu PKK Desa Karang Bunga.</p><p>Tak ketinggalan Penilaian Perlombaan Desa Tingkat Provinsi Kalsel di Desa Karang Bunga juga menampilkan hiburan tradisional reog dan jaranan serta penyerahan hadiah Lomba Desa Tingkat Batola oleh Bupati Hj Noormiliyani.</p><p><br><br></p><p><br></p>', '01K9T6PXAGCE2E5YYNST58P45K.webp', 'featured', 1, 5, 'desa-karang-bunga-masuk-tahapan-penilaian-provinsi', NULL, '2024-12-31 23:09:49', '2025-11-12 02:50:30'),
(3, 'The Lost Art of Political Retirement', '<p>Why don’t politicians ride off into the sunset anymore?<figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:533,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/1*vDSn-_YQJV5Zmvp-Z5F8Ow.jpeg&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:800}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Trump waves to supporters in 2020 (public domain)&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/1*vDSn-_YQJV5Zmvp-Z5F8Ow.jpeg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited\">Trump waves to supporters in 2020 (public domain)</figcaption></figure>James K. Polk thought four years was plenty.</p><p>In 1849, wrote in his <a href=\"https://www.whitehousehistory.org/comfort-in-my-retirement\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">diary</span></a> that</p><blockquote>[My presidency has] been four years of incessant labour and anxiety and of great responsibility. I am heartily rejoiced that my term is so near its close. I will soon cease to be a servant and will become a sovereign. As a private citizen I will have no one but myself to serve, and will exercise a part of the sovereign power of my country. I am sure I will be happier in this condition than in the exalted station I now hold.</blockquote><p>Polk wasn’t old — he was only 53 at the end of his term, the youngest president ever elected up to that point. He wasn’t term-limited either, nor was he beset by scandal and likely to lose re-election. It was just that he didn’t want more than four years in the White House.</p><p>Perhaps it had something to do with his unlikely path to the presidency. After serving in Congress for a couple of terms, Polk had become the governor of Tennessee, which at the time was a relatively powerless office. He lost re-election bids in 1841 and 1843, and it looked like his political career might be over. He decided to take one last shot — a quiet campaign to secure the nomination as Martin Van Buren’s running mate in 1844.</p><p>But a funny thing happened at the convention in Baltimore. Van Buren couldn’t get enough votes to secure the nomination because Southern Democrats aligned behind Lewis Cass, denying Van Buren the two-thirds majority he needed. After eight deadlocked ballots, party elites looked for someone who would be palatable to the entire party, and they settled on James K. Polk. He accepted the nomination, but pledged to be a one-term president.<figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:971,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/1*RWAarn397s8jKCQ1D4Irbg.jpeg&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:800}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Polk, sporting some pretty long hair for a president (public domain)&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/1*RWAarn397s8jKCQ1D4Irbg.jpeg\" width=\"800\" height=\"971\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited\">Polk, sporting some pretty long hair for a president (public domain)</figcaption></figure>Today, this might seem like a path to political impotence — a lame-duck president from day one! But Polk is widely considered to have been a <a href=\"https://www.politico.com/news/magazine/2022/12/02/biden-president-james-k-polk-reelection-00071709\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">good and effective president</span></a>, settling territorial questions in the Oregon Territory, annexing Texas, and winning the Mexican-American War (in which the United States conquered the Southwestern states).</p><p>Polk accomplished so much because he worked incredibly hard during his four years in office, putting in <a href=\"https://www.whitehousehistory.org/comfort-in-my-retirement\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">17-hour days</span></a> and taking less than four weeks off during his time in office. Then, after four years, he was done — ready to retire to his estate in Nashville, happy to rid himself of the work and responsibility that seems to have so burdened him during his time in Washington (sadly, it was a very short retirement — he caught cholera and died a few months after leaving office).</p><p>One wonders what Polk might have to say to our political class, which seems so eager to cling to power today. What might he think of our 82-year-old current president, who had to be forced against his will to leave the race despite clear signs that he was <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/politics/biden-white-house-age-function-diminished-3906a839\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">declining</span></a>? Or of the 78-year-old president-elect, who will supplant Biden as the <a href=\"https://apnews.com/article/trump-harris-presidential-election-age-health-medical-records-7bb8212c1024748371e43b85e137bae5\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">oldest president in history</span></a>? Or the members of the House (whose members’ <a href=\"https://www.nbcnews.com/data-graphics/118th-congress-age-third-oldest-1789-rcna64117\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">median age</span></a> has increased by 9 years since 1980) and the Senate (which has gotten 12 years older)?</p><p>What happened to the lost art of political retirement?</p><p>Perhaps the most important thing George Washington did as president was quit. Among the precedents he set — choosing a cabinet, setting the United States on a course toward neutrality, and putting down the Whiskey Rebellion — was the graceful and dignified way in which he laid down power.</p><p>At the end of his second term in office, Washington was 64 years old. He knew he could almost certainly win a third term if he wanted to — he had only increased the immense respect the American public felt for him. But he also knew that, if he stayed in office until he died, Americans might come to think of the presidency as a lifetime appointment rather than a temporary position.</p><p>On top of that, Washington was <a href=\"https://www.mountvernon.org/george-washington/the-first-president/the-farewell-address\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">tired</span></a>; he wanted to return to Virginia and live a quieter life as a farmer. Four years later, when a friend tried to get him back into politics, he declined, <a href=\"https://www.gilderlehrman.org/history-resources/spotlight-primary-source/washington-proposed-third-term-and-political-parties\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">writing</span></a> that he had “ardent wishes to pass through the vale of life in retirement [sic], undisturbed in the remnant of the days I have to sojourn here.”</p><p>Washington’s decision to leave public life solidified his position as an <a href=\"https://worldhistory.substack.com/p/a-multiplicity-of-george-washingtons?r=7ecn0\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">American icon</span></a>. It set a precedent that held for a century and a half — but why? In our chaotic age of politics, in which <a href=\"https://readmedium.com/wait-its-all-norms-83d0a3c048c3\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">norms</span></a> are being shredded left and right, it’s useful to look at how our political system used to maintain norms around political retirement.</p><p>The first ingredient was self-restraint. Presidents who aspired to more than two terms had to ask themselves whether they thought they were more deserving of a third term than the Founding Father himself. For many politicians, this was enough to curb their desire for more time in office, especially in a culture that prized <a href=\"https://readmedium.com/how-american-politics-lost-its-dignity-d33a24d99a1a\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">political dignity</span></a> and punished obvious ambition.</p><p>But you won’t be surprised to learn that many politicians <em>were</em> ambitious (though they had to keep it hidden) and <em>did</em> think they were better than George Washington! So the norm required more than simple self-discipline; it needed political elites to enforce it.</p><p>This happened a few times when presidents flirted with third terms. Ulysses S. Grant was the first to try to stay in office longer than eight years. He floated the idea toward the end of his second term, but his fellow Republicans in Congress made it clear that they did not support his breaking the norm. Seeing this opposition, he took a <em>you-can’t-fire-me-I-quit</em> approach, declining to seek the nomination in 1876. He <a href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/quotes/8872852-julia-would-gladly-have-stayed-for-one-more-term-and\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">told</span></a> his wife, perhaps unconvincingly, “I do not want to be here [Washington] another four years. I do not think I could stand it.”<figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:633,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/1*hOf4CQX_LiiTLTcytAY2cQ.jpeg&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:800}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Grant surrencers his attempt to serve a third term (LOC)&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/1*hOf4CQX_LiiTLTcytAY2cQ.jpeg\" width=\"800\" height=\"633\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited\">Grant surrencers his attempt to serve a third term (LOC)</figcaption></figure>After a post-election trip around the world, Grant tried to come right back to the White House. He had a lot of support at the Republican Convention of 1880 — his supporters played on his role in the Civil War, calling him the candidate from Appomattox. His opponents, who coalesced around James Garfield, worried about Grant’s ambition to break Washington’s two-term precedent. It was a close-run thing: Grant got the most votes (though not enough to clinch the nomination) on the first 35 ballots; it was only on the 36th that the opponents of a third term united behind Garfield and ended Grant’s political career.<figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:1066,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/0*RTs-e6ZqJ77QH7Cg.jpg&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:800}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;The ghost of George Washington shames Theodore Roosevelt (National Archives)&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/0*RTs-e6ZqJ77QH7Cg.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"1066\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited\">The ghost of George Washington shames Theodore Roosevelt (National Archives)</figcaption></figure>Theodore Roosevelt also tried to break Washington’s precedent by re-entering politics in the 1912 election. Like Grant, he had stepped down after two terms in office and handed the presidency to his protege William Howard Taft. But Taft proved more conservative than Roosevelt had hoped, so Roosevelt jumped back into politics.</p><p>In 1912, Roosevelt was popular, winning most of the primaries that were held that year. But as had happened in 1880, the Republican Party’s political elites stood firm against a third term for Roosevelt (and in favor of Taft, the incumbent president). Once it became clear that he couldn’t win the GOP nomination, Roosevelt ran as a third-party candidate but lost the election.<figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:878,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/0*-KLnmZSNWxELhqFe&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:685}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A satirical sculpture showing FDR as a sphinx who wouldn’t say whether he was running again (National Archives)&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.readmedium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/0*-KLnmZSNWxELhqFe\" width=\"685\" height=\"878\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited\">A satirical sculpture showing FDR as a sphinx who wouldn’t say whether he was running again (National Archives)</figcaption></figure>It wasn’t until 1940 when, amid a depression and a growing global crisis, Democrats nominated Franklin Roosevelt for a third run at the presidency. Even when violating the norm, FDR tried to make it look like he didn’t want to stay in office. He refused to signal whether he would run, insisting that Democrats <a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/story/a-third-term-u-s-national-archives/ZwWBBatPTBcA8A?hl=en\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">draft</span></a> him. They did, but not without a bitter and lengthy standoff. FDR would serve a third term, then run again despite visible <a href=\"https://worldhistory.medium.com/one-last-campaign-c50f664d7300\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">signs of decline</span></a>, before dying in office a few months into his fourth term.</p><p>Though the presidency has gotten the most attention in our debates over age, politics, and retirement, there are worrying trends in other branches of government, as well.</p><p>I’ve already mentioned that Congress is getting older, and the <a href=\"https://www.senate.gov/senators/longest_serving_senators.htm\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">list of longest-serving</span></a> members of Congress is overwhelmingly populated with recent officeholders. Given changes in life expectancy, this isn’t altogether surprising, but it has led to two problems.</p><p>First, the longer older politicians hang onto power, the more frustrated younger voters become. They’ve come to view the government as <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/14/opinion/america-gerontocracy-biden-trump.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">unrepresentative</span></a>, more interested in cementing the advantages that older people already have rather than looking forward. It’s part of the reason why only a quarter of young people <a href=\"https://thenext100.org/young-adults-think-americas-political-system-isnt-working/\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">think</span></a> our political system is working well and only half of them think democracy is a good system of government.</p><p>Second, elderly politicians who hang on too long create uncomfortable questions about their health and fitness for office. During her final years in office before her death at age 90, many observers felt that California Senator <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2023/09/29/us/politics/dianne-feinstein-obituary.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Dianne Feinstein</span></a> was not up to the job. You may have caught a recent controversy over whether an 81-year-old <a href=\"https://www.yahoo.com/news/d-c-age-debate-reignites-223516939.html?guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&amp;guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAJ0sCh-8Lk-eNE5ZMBy3cHS8waf6qF2G0ROHCtHy1xjLdbaOPs_Mv5SOBzbE7XF1tHsHYrdWLHEyCXYjLhLbSDjjxlRWdRgGlchAp6qHyYEuWDK4DFUKhZjIpJ7qO-QAsJxHdCThCMsij_LCWAbP_HH-BOUThBA4IJgaS6PBl6OE\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">House member</span></a> was actually living in a memory care facility while in office or just had “dementia issues,” as her son put it. And the average Supreme Court justice now stays on the bench for <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/14/opinion/america-gerontocracy-biden-trump.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">a decade longer</span></a> than they did before 1970. When <a href=\"https://www.politico.com/news/magazine/2022/06/10/ruth-bader-ginsburg-retire-legacy-00038638\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ruth Bader Ginsburg</span></a> decided to stay on the Court into her late 80s, her death allowed Donald Trump to secure a conservative majority on the court for a generation.</p><p>So what should be done? One answer would be to develop new norms around political aspiration. Americans used to want politicians who weren’t dripping with ambition. They were supposed to pretend, at least, that they weren’t desperate to wield power, that high office was an act of service rather than self-aggrandizement. Under that set of expectations, it was harder for politicians to overstay their welcome.</p><p>A second solution might be to strengthen parties. As we’ve seen, parties held the line against candidates who wanted to break Washington’s two-term precedent. They could step in today to refuse to nominate the same people over and over again. Either on grounds of age or because it would be politically advantageous to freshen their rosters with new talent, parties might decide to force retirement on those who won’t choose it for themselves.</p><p>Finally, we might look to legislation. After FDR, Congress replaced the norms that had governed presidential politics with a law — the 22nd Amendment forced presidents to do what people like George Washington and James Polk had once done voluntarily. This idea is incredibly popular with the American public — 87% of Americans want <a href=\"https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2023/09/19/how-americans-view-proposals-to-change-the-political-system/\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Congressional term limits</span></a>, 79% want an age limit for elected officials, and 69% want a “<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2024/09/13/supreme-court-term-limits-justices-poll/\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">mandatory retirement age</span></a>” for the Supreme Court.</p><p>Of the three solutions, the legal one seems the most likely. New laws around political retirement would likely not be perfect, but they’d be an improvement. American voters want them — but will one of the oldest groups of legislators in history vote to loosen their own grip on power?</p><p><em>Thanks for reading! If you’d like to receive an email whenever I publish an article, click </em><a href=\"https://worldhistory.medium.com/subscribe\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">here</span></a><em>. I also write </em><a href=\"http://worldhistory.substack.com/\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Looking Through the Past</span></a><em>, a newsletter about historical artifacts and images — check it out! You can “buy me a cup of coffee” </em><a href=\"https://ko-fi.com/georgedillard\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">here</span></a><em>.</em></p><p><br></p>', '01JGDRS8MA833GY4XA6B7XDNCM.jpg', 'not_featured', 0, 4, 'the-lost-art-of-political-retirement', '2025-11-11 18:29:50', '2024-12-31 23:09:49', '2025-11-11 18:29:50'),
(4, 'Desa Karang Bunga Kabupaten Barito Kuala Jadi Tujuan Praktik Kampus Merdeka Belajar', '<p><strong>MARABAHAN</strong> - Desa Karang Bunga, Kecamatan Mandastana, <a href=\"https://banjarmasin.tribunnews.com/tag/kabupaten-barito-kuala\">Kabupaten Barito Kuala</a> (Batola), Provinsi Kalimantan Selatan (Kalsel), berhasil mengembangkan berbagai potensi alamnya.<br>Karena itu, desa di Kabupaten <a href=\"https://banjarmasin.tribunnews.com/tag/batola\">Batola</a> ini menjadi tujuan praktik pertukaran mahasiswa yang dikemas dengan nama Pertukaran Mahasiswa Kampus Merdeka Belajar oleh <a href=\"https://banjarmasin.tribunnews.com/tag/universitas-lambung-mangkurat\">Universitas Lambung Mangkurat</a> (ULM). <br>Disampaikan Agus Supriadi, Sekretaris <a href=\"https://banjarmasin.tribunnews.com/tag/desa-karang-bunga\">Desa Karang Bunga</a>, sebanyak 25 mahasiswa dari berbagai kampus di Indonesia berkumpul di desanya untuk menjalankan program tersebut. <br>\"Ada berbagai kegiatan yang digelar, di antaranya adalah membuat es krim jeruk dan mengenal agroeduwisata kebun jeruk,\" bebernya, Sabtu (24/12/2022). <br><br><br>Artikel ini telah tayang di <a href=\"https:\">BanjarmasinPost.co.id</a> dengan judul Desa Karang Bunga Kabupaten Barito Kuala Jadi Tujuan Praktik Kampus Merdeka Belajar, <a href=\"https://banjarmasin.tribunnews.com/2022/12/25/desa-karang-bunga-kabupaten-barito-kuala-jadi-tujuan-praktik-kampus-merdeka-belajar\">https://banjarmasin.tribunnews.com/2022/12/25/desa-karang-bunga-kabupaten-barito-kuala-jadi-tujuan-praktik-kampus-merdeka-belajar</a>.<br>Penulis: Muhammad Tabri | Editor: Alpri Widianjono</p><p>Pihaknya merasa bangga bisa menjadi salah satu desa yang ditunjuk menjadi lokasi praktik pertukaran mahasiswa tingkat nasional ini.&nbsp;</p><p>Menurutnya, dengan kurikulum merdeka yang diterapkan, terjun langsung ke lapangan adalah metode yang tepat untuk belajar dengan efektif.&nbsp;</p><p>\"Mereka mendapatkannya secara langsung, tidak berkutat dengan banyak teori,\" ceplosnya.&nbsp;</p><p>Dia pun menambahkan, kesan para mahasiswa yang bertandang ke desanya merasa sangat antusias.</p>', '01K9TXGJQ3Q8V3812M73VJMSA4.jpg', 'not_featured', 1, 6, 'desa-karang-bunga-kabupaten-barito-kuala-jadi-tujuan-praktik-kampus-merdeka-belajar', NULL, '2024-12-30 18:53:44', '2025-11-12 03:01:17'),
(5, 'I Wrote On LinkedIn for 100 Days', '<h3>Everyone is hiring.Introduction</h3><p><figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;filename&quot;:&quot;nguyen-dang-hoang-nhu-dYUQI3dM4R4-unsplash.jpg&quot;,&quot;filesize&quot;:913233,&quot;height&quot;:3456,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;http://127.0.0.1:8000/storage/Lc4rHxzVdsLL0WvrEp38CJ4Vu7giH3U6X1QDUWDa.jpg&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;http://127.0.0.1:8000/storage/Lc4rHxzVdsLL0WvrEp38CJ4Vu7giH3U6X1QDUWDa.jpg&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:5184}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;presentation&quot;:&quot;gallery&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview attachment--jpg\"><a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8000/storage/Lc4rHxzVdsLL0WvrEp38CJ4Vu7giH3U6X1QDUWDa.jpg\"><img src=\"http://127.0.0.1:8000/storage/Lc4rHxzVdsLL0WvrEp38CJ4Vu7giH3U6X1QDUWDa.jpg\" width=\"5184\" height=\"3456\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption\"><span class=\"attachment__name\">nguyen-dang-hoang-nhu-dYUQI3dM4R4-unsplash.jpg</span> <span class=\"attachment__size\">891.83 KB</span></figcaption></a></figure>In 2020, I read a book called the Power of Habit and challenged myself to try something new. As someone who’s an introvert and felt shy about sharing my thoughts, one of the habits I wanted to work on was speaking up more.</p><p>I read the book in a few days and one of the key points it pointed out was that the best way to do something is to tell everyone else about it.</p><p>Apparently the social peer pressure helps. So I decided to write on LinkedIn, a space where nobody really knew who I was.</p><p>I made a random challenge to myself that I would write on the platform for 100 days straight. Sure it was a weird challenge, but I figured it’d at least help with finding a job as an unemployed university student.</p><p>It was one of the hardest things I’ve ever done in my life.</p><h3>Day 1</h3><p>Pressing post for the first time was a spooky experience. It feels like everyone is going to judge you for saying anything, even though most people are just casually scrolling through their feed.</p><p>I made it public to everyone that this would be a 100 day commitment by ending every LinkedIn post with the post number. First one down and 99 more to go.</p><p><strong>1 of 100</strong></p><h3>Day 2 to Day 10 — What do you even talk about?</h3><p>After the first day I regretted the challenge. It’s like forcing yourself to go to the gym when you really don’t want to.</p><p>My biggest challenge was that I had 0 idea what to write about. Sure nobody really knew I made this self inflicted challenge to myself, but it would hurt my ego to suddenly give up.</p><p>I forced myself to come up with something and I ran with random things that happened to me that day.</p><p>Things like getting annoyed waiting in line for the cashier, struggling with math homework, my life living at home.</p><p>I literally had no direction with my content but I just had to keep going with he challenge.</p><p><strong>10 of 100</strong></p><h3>Day 11 to Day 30 — Cater to the platform</h3><p>After 10 days of posting, the post button suddenly stops getting scary. It was just hard thinking about a good idea to post about.</p><p>I had to catch myself why I cared about the audience reading my content. It felt like if I was getting ignored then I was doing something wrong.</p><p>With 10 days worth of content, I noticed the post about struggling with math did a little bit better than my other posts. I wouldn’t know it at the time but having a struggle and trying to overcome it is a relatable story for everyone.</p><p>If I wanted to get noticed a little more, I focused my topics about challenges I had in life. Building healthy habits, waking up early, finding a job, and making friends.</p><p>Talking about problems is easy and not all of those posts did well. But it gave me something to write about everyday.</p><p>Of course, I always felt like I could be doing better.</p><p><strong>30 of 100</strong></p><h3>Day 30 to Day 50 — People are following the journey</h3><p>After writing for 30 days, I started to see comments from people talking about how they just binged my random posts from every other day.</p><p>That gave me the sense that people were interested in the journey, even if they’re not clicking the like button. Giving everyone a clear goal to follow along gave my audience a reason to come back to see what I’m going to write next.</p><p>The problem with this was that it made me feel pressured to live up to the expectations to write engaging content. Talking about problems helps but I noticed some problems were better topics than others.</p><p>The most popular topic was about finding a job.</p><p>I started to shift content from my daily activities to posting about what the job market has been like for me. Little did I know it would resonate with a lot of people who also struggled with the job market.</p><p>It was nice for everyone to have someone they could relate to and voice the struggles of being unemployed.</p><p>Suddenly I became known as an aspiring software engineer who was eager to learn more. It was great… until I started to burn out.</p><p><strong>Day 50 of 100</strong></p><h3>Day 51 to Day 80 — It wasn’t fun anymore</h3><p>Nobody wants to eat the same thing everyday. Similarly, talking about the same topics can get boring, especially if nothing new is happening.</p><p>I shared stories about how I was struggling with the job market but that was the end of it. As relatable as it was, I felt like I needed to make it more interesting for myself.</p><p>This is backwards from what most content creators will tell you because if something works, don’t fix it. Just farm it.</p><p>I didn’t know this was the common content creator mindset but I didn’t want to be boxed as the job struggle guy, so I talked about all the cool things you could do with software engineering.</p><p>I was a computer science major after all so I thought that instead of talking about problems, I can teach people what I’m learning. Maybe it’d help someone else.</p><p>My following grew and what I didn’t expect was that I was getting reached out to by recruiters. They saw some of my posts and invited me to interview with some really large tech companies.</p><p>I will say that marketing your skills makes it easier to find people interested in them. All I needed to do now was to close out the rest of the 100 day challenge.</p><p><strong>80 of 100</strong></p><h3>Day 81 to Day 99— Pressure to keep improving</h3><p>Every day I felt pressure to make a post that would out perform the last. More people are following the journey, more readers are leaving comments.</p><p>It was a result of writing about popular LinkedIn topics and iterating on every post I was writing on.</p><p>But the social pressure was intense because it felt like there were so many eyes on my content for the first time. It was the first time anyone saw anything like this on LinkedIn.</p><p>After running out of my own ideas, I made the brave decision to look at what other people were writing. I needed their inspiration to think about what I could write about.</p><p>It became problematic. I couldn’t write about the topics other writers wrote on the platform like doing b2b sales or leading an engineering team. So I fell back on what I was feeling.</p><p>Stress, anxiety, and other problems I was facing in life. I wanted to share stories that were relatable with other people again because that’s what I enjoyed the most.</p><p>It almost got me to the end. But I had no idea how I would cap off the 100th day.</p><p><strong>99 of 100</strong></p><h3>Day 100 — Thank you</h3><p>To everyone who followed me on that journey, I realized the proper way to send it off was to thank everyone who went through the experience with me.</p><p>From the emotional turmoil of being lost about what to write about to improving on every post, it was an adventure most people couldn’t imagine going through.</p><p>From everything I learned about writing on LinkedIn for 100 days, I saw that software engineering topics did exceedingly well. The more I touched on those topics, the more recruiters would reach out without even seeing my resume.</p><p>Although I’m not in that space anymore, I could always go back to it if I needed to find another job as a software engineer.</p>', '01JGDAMEWME4HMY7X9KET5W8NA.jpg', 'not_featured', 0, 3, 'i-wrote-on-linkedin-for-100-days', '2025-11-11 18:29:50', '2024-12-31 23:09:49', '2025-11-11 18:29:50'),
(6, 'Foods high in alkali aid in weight loss, boost immunity, and strengthen bones.', '<p>Alkaline foods have unique health benefits, particularly for middle-aged and older people. Or are they just the kind of harmless promotional ads that food and pharmaceutical corporations have always used to increase their profits, avoiding a lot of legal issues in the process?</p><p>I specifically developed this post in response to requests from numerous friends on the site for a unique topic regarding foods high in alkali.</p><p>Eating these foods promotes overall health, including bone health and weight loss, and helps the body restore its pH balance, according to medical nutritional research and studies.</p><p>It is thought that eating alkaline foods — which are often plant-based and low in acid-forming substances — will aid in restoring the pH balance of the body and improving general health. When the pH is between 7.35 and 7.45, or alkaline, the human body performs at its peak.</p><p><figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image/webp&quot;,&quot;filename&quot;:&quot;1_oBIfBm46xDXKHznDlQb2fg.webp&quot;,&quot;filesize&quot;:31942,&quot;height&quot;:960,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;http://127.0.0.1:8000/storage/Gac3JtzMfMWcSxpdldg3byvzEaBE4cPLogg85RKg.webp&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;http://127.0.0.1:8000/storage/Gac3JtzMfMWcSxpdldg3byvzEaBE4cPLogg85RKg.webp&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:640}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image/webp\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;presentation&quot;:&quot;gallery&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview attachment--webp\"><a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8000/storage/Gac3JtzMfMWcSxpdldg3byvzEaBE4cPLogg85RKg.webp\"><img src=\"http://127.0.0.1:8000/storage/Gac3JtzMfMWcSxpdldg3byvzEaBE4cPLogg85RKg.webp\" width=\"640\" height=\"960\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption\"><span class=\"attachment__name\">1_oBIfBm46xDXKHznDlQb2fg.webp</span> <span class=\"attachment__size\">31.19 KB</span></figcaption></a></figure></p><p>Loss of Weight</p><p>You can support general metabolic function and maintain a healthy weight by including alkaline foods in your diet. Foods high in fiber encourage satiety, which makes you feel fuller for longer and less likely to overeat. Generally speaking, alkaline meals are high in nutrients and low in calories, offering vital vitamins and minerals.</p><p>pH</p><p>The body’s pH level indicates how acidic or alkaline it is. A pH of seven is regarded as neutral; values below seven denote acidity, whereas values above seven denote alkalinity.</p><p>For the best possible cellular function, enzyme activity, and general bodily function, a pH level that is balanced is required.</p><p>Increasing Immune Function</p><p>Keeping the immune system robust is essential for protecting the body from illnesses and infections. Alkaline foods help enhance the immune response, neutralize dangerous free radicals, and lessen chronic inflammation because they are high in immune-boosting nutrients, including antioxidants and vitamins A, C, and E.</p><p>Encourage Bone Health</p><p>While eating acidic meals, including processed meats and refined grains, increases the body’s acid load and causes mineral loss from the bones, eating alkaline foods can help maintain healthy bones.</p><p>Alkaline foods, on the other hand, such tofu and almonds, are high in vital minerals like calcium, magnesium, and potassium that help keep bones strong and lower the risk of osteoporosis.</p><p>bolster the digestive tract</p><p>High in fiber, alkaline foods help to reduce constipation and support a healthy digestive system. Fruits and vegetables, like berries and apples, are great sources of dietary fiber.</p><p>A sufficient diet of fiber also promotes the development of good gut bacteria and aids in the regulation of bowel motions.</p><p>Encourage Bone Health</p><p>While eating acidic meals, including processed meats and refined grains, increases the body’s acid load and causes mineral loss from the bones, eating alkaline foods can help maintain healthy bones.</p><p>Alkaline foods, on the other hand, such tofu and almonds, are high in vital minerals like calcium, magnesium, and potassium that help keep bones strong and lower the risk of osteoporosis.</p><p>bolster the digestive tract</p><p>High in fiber, alkaline foods help to reduce constipation and support a healthy digestive system. Fruits and vegetables, like berries and apples, are great sources of dietary fiber.</p><p>A sufficient diet of fiber also promotes the development of good gut bacteria and aids in the regulation of bowel motions.</p><p>In summary</p><p>In order to maintain balance and lower the body’s acidity, nutritionists advise consuming alkaline meals, including leafy greens, whole grains, legumes, berries, citrus fruits, nuts, seeds, and high-quality organic items.</p>', '01JGDQVJBAA37ER4EVV01FWD9G.jpg', 'featured', 0, 3, 'foods-high-in-alkali-aid-in-weight-loss-boost-immunity-and-strengthen-bones', '2025-11-11 18:29:50', '2024-12-30 22:53:35', '2025-11-11 18:29:50');
INSERT INTO `article_news` (`id`, `name`, `content`, `thumbnail`, `is_featured`, `category_id`, `author_id`, `slug`, `deleted_at`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(7, 'Satu-satunya di Kalsel, Desa Karang Bunga Dinilai untuk Lomba Pangan Aman Tingkat Nasional', '<p>Warga Kabupaten Barito Kuala (Batola) patut berbangga. Pasalnya Desa Karang Bunga, Kecamatan Mandastana, satu-satunya di Kalimantan Selatan yang mendapat penilaian dalam lomba pangan aman ( Lomba Paman) tingkat nasional.<br>Terkait penilaian Lomba Paman tersebut, Tim Verifikasi yang berjumlah empat orang, turun lapangan mengunjungi Desa Karang Bunga, Kamis (09/03/2023).</p><p>Keempat verifikator yang datang ke bumi ‘Ije Jela’ itu yakni Fausta Maria Rochmawati dari Kementrian Desa PDTT, Indriemayatie Asri Ganie dan Dewintha Syandi khairunnisa dari BPOM RI, serta Leonard Duma yang menjabat Kepala BBPOM Banjarmasin.</p><p>Kedatangan tim verifikasi disambut Sekda Ir Zukifili Yadi Noor. Turut hadir Asisten II Setda Batola, Suyud Sugiono, dan sejumlah pimpinan SKPD di lingkungan Pemkab Batola.</p><p>Dalam melakukan tugasnya, tim verifikasi melakukan penilaian di sejumlah titik. Antara lain di kantin sekolah, pelaku usaha pangan siap saji (PKL), dan Ritel/Warung.</p><p>Kemudian tim verifikasi juga menilai proses dan sanitasi UKM masyarakat, warung yang menjadi ruang pajang produk UKM, serta Pamsimas.</p><p>Verifikasi lapangan sendiri merupakan tahapan akhir seleksi Desa Pangan Aman tingkat nasional setelah tahapan administrasi dan wawancara yang telah dilaksanakan dalam kesempatan sebelumnya.</p><p>Sekda Zukifli Yadi Noor mengungkapkan rasa bangganya karena desa Karang Bunga menjadi satu-satunya di Kalsel yang menjadi lokasi penilaian.</p><p>“Kita berharap Desa Karang Bunga dapat juara dalam penilaian pangan aman, dan mengangkat statusnya menjadi desa mandiri, ” harap Sekda.</p><p>Sementara Fausta Maria Rochmawati mewakili tim verifikasi menjelaskan, pihaknya akan mengumpulkan dulu hasil penilaian di seluruh Indonesia. Setelah itu baru dilakukan sidang dengan seluruh tim penilai.<br>“Semoga yang terbaik dapat kabupaten Batola raih, ” ujarnya.</p><p>Adapun desa-desa yang masuk nominator 10 besar Lomba Desa Pangan Aman Tingkat Nasional ini adalah Kelurahan Jerukwudel (DIY), Kelurahan Pancoran (DKI Jakarta), Desa Randusari (Jawa Tengah), Desa Tanjung Lay (Kalimantan Barat), dan Desa Tengin Baru (Kalimantan Timur).</p><p>Selanjut Desa Karang Bunga (Kalimantan Selatan), Desa Mekong (Riau), Kalurahan Galung Maloang (Sulawesi Selatan), Desa Maelang (Sulawesi Utara), dan Desa Lubuk Cuik (Sumatera Selatan)</p>', '01K9TY88E490ERF96FQZME9FNE.webp', 'featured', 4, 5, 'satu-satunya-di-kalsel-desa-karang-bunga-dinilai-untuk-lomba-pangan-aman-tingkat-nasional', NULL, '2024-12-30 23:45:47', '2025-11-12 03:01:59'),
(8, 'MrBeast: Revolutionizing Entertainment and Philanthropy on YouTube', '<p>MrBeast: Revolutionizing Entertainment and Philanthropy on YouTube</p><p>Jimmy Donaldson, widely known as MrBeast, is one of the most influential figures in the digital world. With a unique blend of larger-than-life stunts, philanthropy, and creativity, MrBeast has transformed YouTube into a platform not just for entertainment, but for making a real-world impact. Born on May 7, 1998, in Greenville, North Carolina, MrBeast has risen to global fame as a content creator, entrepreneur, and philanthropist.</p><p>The Rise of a YouTube Phenomenon</p><p>MrBeast began his YouTube journey in 2012, posting gaming content and comedic commentary. However, his breakthrough came with his innovative and extravagant videos, where he started performing outrageous challenges, such as counting to 100,000 or staying underwater for 24 hours. His creative approach to content quickly gained attention, and he began amassing millions of followers.</p><p>Today, his YouTube channel boasts over 200 million subscribers, making it one of the most-subscribed channels in the world. His success can be attributed to his originality, relatability, and an unrelenting drive to push the boundaries of what is possible on the platform.</p><p>Philanthropy at the Core</p><p>What truly sets MrBeast apart is his commitment to philanthropy. He has given away millions of dollars in his videos, often changing the lives of his fans, strangers, and even entire communities. From surprising people with cars and homes to hosting massive cash giveaways, MrBeast’s generosity knows no bounds.</p><p>One of his most notable initiatives is Team Trees, a collaborative effort launched in 2019 with fellow YouTuber Mark Rober. The project aimed to plant 20 million trees worldwide, raising over $20 million in just a few months. Building on this success, he launched Team Seas in 2021, an ambitious campaign to remove 30 million pounds of trash from oceans, rivers, and beaches.</p><p>Business Ventures</p><p>Beyond YouTube, MrBeast has ventured into the business world. He founded Beast Burger, a virtual restaurant chain offering affordable, high-quality burgers across the United States. The brand became an instant hit, with thousands of locations operating through delivery apps. In 2023, he expanded his entrepreneurial reach with Feastables, a snack brand emphasizing sustainability and quality.</p><p>Impact on the Community</p><p>MrBeast’s influence extends far beyond his videos. By using his platform for good, he has inspired countless creators and viewers to engage in acts of kindness and environmental activism. His innovative approach to content creation and philanthropy has redefined the role of a social media influencer.</p><p>Challenges and Controversies</p><p>Despite his success, MrBeast has faced criticism and challenges, including accusations of exploitation or focusing too much on publicity. However, his transparency and genuine passion for helping others have largely overshadowed these critiques, solidifying his reputation as a positive force in the digital space.</p><p>The Future of MrBeast</p><p>As MrBeast continues to break records and innovate, his impact on the entertainment industry and philanthropy is undeniable. Whether he’s planting trees, cleaning oceans, or simply entertaining millions, MrBeast proves that creativity, generosity, and ambition can change the world.</p><p>With his relentless drive and a heart full of generosity, MrBeast remains a beacon of hope and inspiration for millions across the globe. His story is a testament to the power of using one\'s platform to make a difference, proving that success is best measured by the lives we touch.</p>', '01JGDV0530BA7P11TPNPK3MXT8.webp', 'not_featured', 0, 1, 'mrbeast-revolutionizing-entertainment-and-philanthropy-on-youtube', '2025-11-11 18:29:50', '2024-12-30 23:48:31', '2025-11-11 18:29:50'),
(9, 'A Night of Music and Energy That Stands the Test of Time', '<h3>A Six Word Photo Story: Freestyle</h3><h3>Cher’s energy ignited the night — unforgettable!</h3><p>Back in <strong>2014</strong>, my husband and I attended a Cher concert, courtesy of his former company.</p><p>I was completely blown away by Cher’s energy, especially given her age. The show was nothing short of amazing! Between the incredible dance crew, elaborate sets, and all the costume changes, Cher put on a performance that left the audience in awe. She gave it everything she had, and it was an experience I’ll never forget.</p><p>Over the years, my husband’s company gave us the opportunity to go to all kinds of events — professional football and baseball games, and concerts like Florida Georgia Line. Each one was special in its own way and left us with great memories.</p><p><br></p>', '01JGDVF75K5TQQPN59RCNFVZR1.jpg', 'not_featured', 0, 3, 'a-night-of-music-and-energy-that-stands-the-test-of-time', '2025-11-11 18:29:50', '2024-12-30 23:56:45', '2025-11-11 18:29:50'),
(10, 'I Stopped Listening To Music For 30 days - Here’s What I discovered', '<h3>The Beginning</h3><p>Let me give you some context.</p><p>Before my decision to quit listening to music, I was practically addicted to it and couldn’t go a day without it.</p><p>I used music for everything — from motivation for working out to managing stress in times of exams. I was dependent on it.</p><p>I noticed that music had absolute control over me and when I listened to it, I felt transported to another world.</p><p>I used it to cope with all my real-life problems because it allowed me to escape to new worlds in my mind.</p><p>Some people think that’s a good thing, but I’ll explain later why it might be harming you more than benefiting you.</p><h3>What I experienced during those 30 days</h3><p>I didn’t think it would change me that much.</p><p>From the third day, I noticed that my thinking became clearer.</p><p>As I progressed through the 30 days, my performance at school began to improve because I was able to concentrate more and had a sharp mind. I didn’t have random music in my head to distract me from thinking clearly.</p><p>My brain was quiet, I was becoming more mindful of myself and my emotions. I also observed that when I’m meditating, I’m able to focus more and for a longer period of time.</p><p>That’s when my social skills began to improve because I was more present with the other person. I was also able to read more because my mind would be focused on the text rather than drifting elsewhere.</p><p>My mind has become more immune to silence, and I started to seek more peace and nature. I loved spending time in my village in the mountains because the ambiance was peaceful and relaxing.</p><p>For the first time in my life, I avoided crowded and loud places, such as concerts, in favor of quietness.</p><h3>What I discovered</h3><p>I was listening to music because I needed another instant gratification source to help me escape from my problems instead of facing them.</p><p>Such a powerful tool can’t be taken lightly, music has the ability to change emotions and influence one’s perceptions of the world. Listening to it can change our moods within seconds.</p><p>Music is just another source of cheap dopamine, but it’s not discussed much because the music industry generates enormous revenues yearly and is normalized, just as cigarettes were normalized in the past.</p><p>Don’t get me wrong, I don’t mean that the impact of music is comparable to cigarettes, but I do criticize those who, throughout history, have hidden facts for profit.</p><p>People will use music to cope with real-life problems, destroying any sense of responsibility and escaping into a world of melodies and rhythms. This escapism can provide temporary relief but may also lead to a detachment from reality.</p><p>When people ask me what music I listen to and I say that I don’t listen to any, they have all the same reaction. They weren’t used to seeing someone who didn’t listen to music, so they thought I was strange and assumed my life was probably boring.</p><p>What they don’t know is that my life is likely more exciting because I can enjoy anything without music in the background.</p><p>If you quit music too, within 30 days you’ll probably be able to work out and do hard things without needing a bit of music in the background. You will find more motivation overall in your life.</p><p><strong>Remember</strong>,<em> You don’t need external motivation, you are your own motivator.</em></p><p><strong><em>Embrace calmness and mindfulness.</em></strong></p><p><br></p>', '01JGDVPXH11X62KBAP3J96DHJ9.webp', 'not_featured', 0, 3, 'i-stopped-listening-to-music-for-30-days-heres-what-i-discovered', '2025-11-11 18:29:50', '2024-12-31 00:00:57', '2025-11-11 18:29:50'),
(15, 'Kodim 1005/Batola dan Diskopdag Lakukan Peletakan Batu Pertama Gerai Koperasi Merah Putih di Karang Bunga.', '<p><figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;filename&quot;:&quot;1000714628.jpg&quot;,&quot;filesize&quot;:31013,&quot;height&quot;:159,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;http://magayazid.test//storage/2Yg7gJiFd7I3iztWFu2TeYfLIQlOZJMK9szqM7dG.jpg&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;http://magayazid.test//storage/2Yg7gJiFd7I3iztWFu2TeYfLIQlOZJMK9szqM7dG.jpg&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:320}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;presentation&quot;:&quot;gallery&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview attachment--jpg\"><a href=\"http://magayazid.test//storage/2Yg7gJiFd7I3iztWFu2TeYfLIQlOZJMK9szqM7dG.jpg\"><img src=\"http://magayazid.test//storage/2Yg7gJiFd7I3iztWFu2TeYfLIQlOZJMK9szqM7dG.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"159\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption\"><span class=\"attachment__name\">1000714628.jpg</span> <span class=\"attachment__size\">30.29 KB</span></figcaption></a></figure></p><p>MARABAHAN- Komando Distrik Militer (Kodim) 1005/Barito Kuala bersama Dinas Koperasi dan Perdagangan Kabupaten Barito Kuala (Diskopdag Batola) melaksanakan Peletakan Batu Pertama (Groundbreaking) Pembangunan Fisik Gerai Pergudangan dan Kelengkapan Koperasi Desa/Kelurahan Merah Putih di Desa Karang Bunga, Kecamatan Mandastana, Jumat (17/10/2025).</p><p>Kegiatan ini merupakan bagian dari pelaksanaan serentak di 800 Desa/Kelurahan dari 80.000 gerai se-Indonesia yang digelar secara virtual.</p><p>Dalam kesempatan itu, Komandan Kodim 1005/Barito Kuala, Letkol Andika Suseno, menyampaikan bahwa pembangunan fisik Gerai Pergudangan dan Kelengkapan Koperasi Desa/Kelurahan Merah Putih ini menjadi langkah strategis dalam memperkuat ekonomi masyarakat desa.</p><p>“Sebagaimana kita ketahui bersama, koperasi adalah ujung tombak ekonomi desa. Nantinya, melalui koperasi inilah UMKM dan berbagai kegiatan ekonomi akan berkembang,” ujar Letkol Andika Suseno seusai acara peletakan batu pertama.</p><p>Ia menegaskan, pentingnya dukungan dari seluruh pihak dalam menyukseskan program pemerintah pusat tersebut demi kemajuan desa.</p><p>“Dari desa inilah akan tumbuh ekonomi-ekonomi yang kuat, sehingga dapat mendukung ekonomi nasional,” tambah Dandim 1005/Barito Kuala.</p><p>Sementara itu, Kepala Diskopdag Batola, Hery Sasmita, menyampaikan apresiasi dan rasa terima kasih atas sinergi yang dibangun antara Kodim 1005/Barito Kuala dengan pemerintah daerah.</p><p>“Dengan adanya gerakan dari Kodim ini, pemerintah daerah dan masyarakat Barito Kuala merasa sangat terbantu. Pendirian Koperasi Merah Putih di 201 desa di Batola menjadi bukti nyata bahwa kerja sama yang solid dapat mempercepat realisasi program,” ucap Hery.</p><p>Ia menjelaskan, program ini diharapkan menjadi percontohan bagi daerah lain dalam mendorong kemandirian ekonomi masyarakat desa melalui koperasi.</p><p>Acara peletakan batu pertama ini turut dihadiri oleh Kadis DKPP Batola, jajaran Diskopdag Batola, Camat Mandastana, Kapolsek Mandastana, Kepala Desa Karang Bunga, tokoh masyarakat, serta para mahasiswa. (dsk/ali/jp).</p>', '01K9T60BB5HQNCTPC8JHGK7JRF.jpg', 'featured', 3, 2, 'kodim-1005batola-dan-diskopdag-lakukan-peletakan-batu-pertama-gerai-koperasi-merah-putih-di-karang-bunga', NULL, '2025-11-11 11:24:11', '2025-11-12 03:06:41'),
(16, 'Berkat Program BRILian, Desa Karang Bunga Raih Penghargaan Kampung Aman Pangan Nasional', '<p>Sebuah pemandangan tugu berbentuk buah jeruk menyambut ketika tiba di Desa Karang Bunga. Lokasi tersebut terbilang jauh dari Kota Banjarmasin dengan menempuh waktu kurang lebih 45 menit.</p><p>Berjarak 28 kilometer dari Banjarmasin, saat tiba di Desa Karang Bunga, banyak lahan padi dan pohon jeruk yang tumbuh tertata. Meski belum matang, suasana di Desa tersebut terasa sejuk dengan adanya pohon dan jeruk dengan warna hijau natural ini.</p><p>Desa Karang Bunga yang terletak di Kecamatan Mandastana, Kabupaten Barito Kuala, Provinsi Kalimantan Selatan (Kalsel) terpilih sebagai Desa BRILian. Desa yang memiliki luas 60.000 hektare dan penghuni 2.600 jiwa rata-rata hampir 100 persen bekerja sebagai petani, Desa tersebut memiliki potensi dalam peningkatan kesejahteraan ekonomi masyarakat di sektor pertanian.</p><p>Mayoritas para warga di sekitar Desa Karang Bunga bekerja sebagai petani padi dan jeruk. Pemerintah Desa Karang Bunga memperhatikan potensi yang ada untuk meningkatan pendapatan desa. Ditambah lagi dengan dukungan program Desa BRILian yang merupakan program dari Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BRI) yang membantu mewujudkan peningkatan perekonomian desa.</p><p>Selama mengikuti program Desa BRILian, Desa Karang Bunga mendapatkan sejumlah penghargaan. Salah satu penghargaan yang baru-baru ini didapat yakni penghargaan Kampung Aman Pangan tingkat Nasional.</p><p>Sekretaris Desa Karang Bunga, Agus Supriyadi menceritakan, program Desa BRILian masuk ke desa yang dikelolanya sejak akhir 2018 lalu.</p><p>“Setelah bank BRI masuk ke Desa Karang Bunga dan memulai beberapa programnya, kita dari Desa Karang Bunga menyambut baik program – program tersebut. Sejak saat itulah kita kemudian memulai melakukan terobosan-terobosan terutama kaitannya dengan program perekonomian desa,”ujarnya, kepada awak media, Senin (4/3).</p><p>Dia menjelaskan, melalui salah satu Badan Usaha Milik Desa (BUMDes) Berkah Bersama, Desa Karang Bunga memulai program strategis untuk peningkatan pendapatan asli desa dan melakukan kerjasama secara langsung dengan BRI. Salah satu upaya untuk peningkatan salah satu unit usaha BUMDes Berkah Bersama yakni Rumah Produksi Jeruk Karang Bunga.</p><p>“Kemudian meningkatkan penjualan, melalui peningkatan kualitas produk dan kemasan dari berbagai macam olahan Rumah Usaha Jeruk Karang Bunga,” jelasnya.</p><p>Agus mengaku BRI memberikan dukungan luar biasa untuk pembangunan Desa Karang Bunga. Diantaranya yakni bantuan Corporate social responsibility (CSR) Tugu Jeruk yang merupakan ikon dari Desa BRILian dan dan ikon Desa. Bahkan rumah produksi jeruk pun juga merupakan bantuan dari BRI.</p><p>“Selain itu juga memberikan bantuan untuk pembinaan sumber daya manusia terutama umkm dan masyarakat yang terlibat dalam kegiatan produksi dalam pengembangan produk,” bebernya.</p><p>Lebih lanjut lagi, Agus menceritakan Desa Karang Bunga diberikan keistimewaan dengan adanya Desa BRILian. Keistimewaan dari BRI ke Desa Karang Bunga yakni dengan beberapa program CSR seperti beasiswa berprestasi bagi siswa kurang mampu dan peralatan untuk rumah produksi jeruk.</p><p>Kemudian, Desa Karang Bunga juga mendapatkan bantuan khusus untuk klaster padi yang merupakan salah satu klaster yang memiliki potensi luar biasa.</p><p>Dengan program Desa BRILian, Agus mengaku banyak terjadi perubahan pada masyarakat desa sekitar. Masyarakat yang memerlukan bantuan permodalan mendapatkan akses&nbsp; yang lebih mudah dan cepat melalui BRI.</p><p>“Artinya memang kita&nbsp; menjalin kerjasama bukan hanya pada pemerintah, melainkan juga swasta dalam hal ini BRI BUMN yang memberikan dampak yang luar biasa terhadap desa, desa mendapatkan prestasi, salah satunya yang terbaru menjadi Kampung Aman Pangan&nbsp; tingkat Nasional,” terangnya.</p><p>Pimpinan Cabang BRI Marabahan Edwin Agus Franico Sipayung mengatakan, Desa Karang Bunga adalah salah satu contoh sukses BRI dengan melakukan penetrasi produk dan layanan unggulan BRI.</p><p>“Serta berbagai bantuan yang kami salurkan, telah berhasil mendorong peningkatan kapabilitas pengelolaan desa dan BUMDes yang dioptimalkan untuk kesejahteraan masyarakat desa itu sendiri,” ujarnya.</p><p>Lebih lanjut Edwin menjelaskan, BRI juga memberikan dukungan dalam pengembangan soft skill berupa pelatihan masyarakat.</p><p>“Hal-hal tersebut kami lakukan secara bertahap dan berkesinambungan, diinisiasi sejak tahun 2019, mulai diimplementasikan di 2020, dan terus berlangsung sampai saat ini,” tambahnya.</p><p>Edwin mengaku proses pembinaan Desa Karang Bunga sebagai Desa BRILian bukan proses yang sebentar. Dirinya sadar masih banyak potensi di Desa BRILian Karang Bunga yang perlu digali dan terus dikembangkan hingga menjadi desa yang unggul dan berdaya saing.</p><p>“Mengingat kehadiran BRI tidak dapat dipisahkan dalam setiap perkembangan yang terjadi di Desa BRILian Karang Bunga, oleh karena itu saya pastikan bahwa BRI Cabang Marabahan masih akan tetap pada komitmen kami untuk terus hadir membersamai perkembangan Desa BRILian Karang Bunga kedepannya,” imbuhnya.</p><p>Dia menjelaskan, sejak pengimplementasian program Desa BRILian di Desa Karang Bunga berbagai batuan yang diberikan yakni bantuan pembangunan rumah produksi jeruk dan tugu jeruk pada tahun 2022 dengan nilai bantuan nilai bantuan sebesar Rp 232.667.825,-.</p><p>Selain itu, bantuan yang diberikan dalam program Desa BRILian yakni program pemberdayaan produk cluster UMKM Jeruk berupa pelatihan dan Bantuan Peralatan Produksi Peruk pada tahun 2022 dengan nilai bantuan sebesar Rp 50.000.000,-.</p><p>Kemudian bantuan lainnya yakni program pengembangan cluster unggulan padi Sri Bahagia untuk Desa Karang Bunga pada tahun 2023 berupa pelatihan dan penyerahan bantuan alat semprot Electric Battery Sprayer sebanyak 60 unit, dengan nilai bantuan Rp 50.000.000,-.</p><p>”Dari sudut pandang kami, pelaksanaan program Desa BRILian Karang Bunga sudah sesuai target, dimana sejak adanya program ini, telah ada peningkatan ekonomi masyarakat dan peningkatan peningkatan kontribusi Pendapatan Asli Daerah atau PAD dari BUMDes dan kegiatan ekonomi masyarakat yang tidak bisa dilepaskan dari adanya program Desa BRILian ini,” ungkapnya.</p>', '01K9V4S8W39KHA54DF563MYCQ6.jpg', 'not_featured', 1, 3, 'berkat-program-brilian-desa-karang-bunga-raih-penghargaan-kampung-aman-pangan-nasional', NULL, '2025-11-11 20:22:05', '2025-11-12 03:21:08'),
(17, 'Klaster Jeruk Siam Desa Karang Bunga Masuk Unggulan', '<p><figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image/webp&quot;,&quot;filename&quot;:&quot;8-4klm-3.webp&quot;,&quot;filesize&quot;:50024,&quot;height&quot;:328,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;http://karang_bunga_post.test//storage/fnIUjtXGaBO9MoFsthKYg10rVUuPetWIZLL3a8fO.webp&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;http://karang_bunga_post.test//storage/fnIUjtXGaBO9MoFsthKYg10rVUuPetWIZLL3a8fO.webp&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:500}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image/webp\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;presentation&quot;:&quot;gallery&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview attachment--webp\"><a href=\"http://karang_bunga_post.test//storage/fnIUjtXGaBO9MoFsthKYg10rVUuPetWIZLL3a8fO.webp\"><img src=\"http://karang_bunga_post.test//storage/fnIUjtXGaBO9MoFsthKYg10rVUuPetWIZLL3a8fO.webp\" width=\"500\" height=\"328\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption\"><span class=\"attachment__name\">8-4klm-3.webp</span> <span class=\"attachment__size\">48.85 KB</span></figcaption></a></figure> MENINGKAT - Dengan pinjaman modal dari BRI, petani mampu meningkatkan hasil perkebunan jeruk serta potensi keuntungan klaster menjadi lebih besar sehingga kesejahteraan anggota dapat terjamin. (KP/Istimewa) Dengan pinjaman modal dari BRI, petani mampu meningkatkan hasil perkebunan jeruk serta potensi keuntungan klaster menjadi lebih besar sehingga kesejahteraan anggota dapat terjamin. MARABAHAN, KP – Desa Karang Bunga berhasil mengikuti event nasional dengan produk unggulan Jeruk Siam. Seiring itu, BRI Marabahan pun sukses tembus ke dalam event nasional yang diadakan oleh BRI Kantor Pusat sebagai salah satu dari 5 Klaster terpilih di seluruh Indonesia. 1/3 Klaster Jeruk Siam dari Desa Karang Bunga, Kecamatan Mandastana, Kabupaten Barito Kuala, Kalimantan Selatan, merupakan salah satu klaster unggulan yang ada di Barito Kuala, seperti yang disampaikan kepada KP, kemarin. Produk olahan yang dihasilkan dari jeruk Desa Karang Bunga adalah berupa es krim dengan label Antani. Selain itu juga terdapat produk unggulan lain, yaitu padi lokal. Berawal dari potensi desa yang mayoritas masyarakatnya petani jeruk dan dikelola secara individu yang kemudian akhirnya membentuk klaster usaha di awal tahun 2021 dan beranggotakan 33 orang. Sedangkan, salah satu permasalahan petani jeruk adalah perawatan masa produksi pada tanaman jeruk. Karena jeruk memerlukan perawatan khusus dengan biaya cukup besar, mulai dari pemupukan, penyemprotan dan perlindungan buah agar tidak rusak dari serangan hama lalat buah. Di sini BRI pun berperan, khususnya BRI Unit Sungai Gampa Kantor Cabang marabahan memberi dukungan berupa permodalan KUR dan Kupedes, serta layanan perbankan lainnya. Dengan pinjaman modal dari BRI, petani mampu meningkatkan hasil perkebunan jeruk serta potensi keuntungan klaster menjadi lebih besar sehingga kesejahteraan anggota dapat terjamin. BRI juga memfasilitasi studi banding untuk aparat desa yang sekaligus merangkap sebagai ketua BUMDes ke Semarang untuk kemajuan desanya, serta pelatihan untuk kelempok petani jeruk. 2/3 Baca Juga : BRI Serahkan Bantuan 8 Unit Tempat Tidur Pasien untuk RS Bhayangkara Banjarmasin Ibu Santi sapaan akrabnya, merupakan salah seorang warga Desa Karang Bunga pemilik Agen Brilink Arto Podo Moro sekaligus sebagai Ketua Klaster Jeruk. Dia memulai karirnya sebagai petani jeruk dan kemudian bekerja sama dengan BRI sebagai Agen Brilink, yang sekarang sukses mengembangkan usahanya hingga memiliki toko buah dan sembako. Bahkan, saat ini ia juga memiliki 20 ekor sapi yang semula hanya 5 ekor sapi. Dengan kelolaan BRI Unit Sungan Gampa, Ibu Santi sangat berterima kasih atas support dari BRI berupa pinjaman dana KUR hingga terfasilitasi dalam pengelolaan usahanya sampai saat ini. (Opq/K-1)&nbsp;</p>', '01K9V4Z9C23CMG9G9ZA3A8B97M.webp', 'not_featured', 4, 4, 'klaster-jeruk-siam-desa-karang-bunga-masuk-unggulan', NULL, '2025-11-11 20:25:22', '2025-11-12 03:03:42'),
(18, 'Desa Karang Bunga Terima Penghargaan Desa Terbaik Nasional', '<p><figure data-trix-attachment=\"{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image/webp&quot;,&quot;filename&quot;:&quot;821d0ba6849229b1cfac6b73fdc00935.webp&quot;,&quot;filesize&quot;:55062,&quot;height&quot;:520,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;http://karang_bunga_post.test//storage/H2e7UTXhzoI3ULxoMYHbGdZNc8rv9lMlurd24zq7.webp&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;http://karang_bunga_post.test//storage/H2e7UTXhzoI3ULxoMYHbGdZNc8rv9lMlurd24zq7.webp&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:750}\" data-trix-content-type=\"image/webp\" data-trix-attributes=\"{&quot;presentation&quot;:&quot;gallery&quot;}\" class=\"attachment attachment--preview attachment--webp\"><a href=\"http://karang_bunga_post.test//storage/H2e7UTXhzoI3ULxoMYHbGdZNc8rv9lMlurd24zq7.webp\"><img src=\"http://karang_bunga_post.test//storage/H2e7UTXhzoI3ULxoMYHbGdZNc8rv9lMlurd24zq7.webp\" width=\"750\" height=\"520\"><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption\"><span class=\"attachment__name\">821d0ba6849229b1cfac6b73fdc00935.webp</span> <span class=\"attachment__size\">53.77 KB</span></figcaption></a></figure></p><p>MARABAHAN - Pemerintah Kabupaten Batola patut berbangga. Salah satu desa di daerah ini mendapatkan penghargaan dari Kementerian Desa, Pembangunan Daerah Tertinggal, dan Transmigrasi RI.</p><p><br></p><p>Desa penerima penghargaan tersebut ialah Karang Bunga, Kecamatan Mandastana. Mendapat penghargaan sebagai Nominasi Desa Terbaik Nasional kategori Penguatan Pembangunan dan Pemberdayaan Masyarakat Tahun 2018.</p><p><br></p><p>Penerimaan penghargaan tersebut diungkapkan Sekretaris Desa Karang Bunga, Agus. Menurut dia, penghargaan diberikan langsung oleh Dirjen Pembangunan dan Pemberdayaan Masyarakat Desa, Taufik Madjid, Kamis (29/11) di Hotel Sultan Jakarta, Jakarta Pusat.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>\"Kepala Desa Karang Bunga, Sarino secara langsung diundang ke Jakarta untuk menerima penghargaan ini, “ ujarnya.</p><p><br></p><p>Selain penghargaan, Agus mengungkapkan mereka juga mendapat uang pembinaan sebesar Rp50 juta untuk Bumdes.</p><p><br></p><p>Sebagai Sekdes Agus mengaku tidak menyangka bakal mendapat penghargaan.</p><p><br></p><p>\"Sebenarnya desa kami biasa saja, tidak ada yang beda dengan desa lain di Kabupaten Batola. Hanya saja kami memiliki perencanaan dan konsep jangka panjang untuk menjadi desa agrowisata. Melalui dana desa dan kemendes kami berupaya mewujudkan itu dengan berbagai inovasi,\" ujarnya</p>', '01K9VA66TK2KERSHZDVYS006HZ.webp', 'not_featured', 3, 1, 'desa-karang-bunga-terima-penghargaan-desa-terbaik-nasional', NULL, '2025-11-11 21:56:32', '2025-11-12 03:04:13'),
(19, 'Sah! APBDes Karang Bunga 2026 Ditetapkan Sebesar Rp 1,9 Miliar, Fokus Pada Jalan Usaha Tani dan Stunting', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Pemerintah Desa (Pemdes) Karang Bunga bersama Badan Permusyawaratan Desa (BPD) secara resmi menetapkan Anggaran Pendapatan dan Belanja Desa (APBDes) untuk tahun anggaran 2026. Dalam Musyawarah Desa (Musdes) yang digelar di Balai Desa hingga Selasa (11/11) malam, disepakati total anggaran sebesar <strong>Rp 1.9 Miliar</strong>.</p><p>Angka ini berasal dari berbagai sumber pendapatan, termasuk Dana Desa (DD) dari APBN, Alokasi Dana Desa (ADD) dari APBD Kabupaten, Pendapatan Asli Desa (PADes) dari BUMDes, serta sumber lainnya. Rapat yang berlangsung alot namun konstruktif ini dihadiri oleh Kepala Desa, seluruh anggota BPD, perwakilan RT/RW, tokoh masyarakat, dan pendamping desa.</p><p>Kepala Desa Karang Bunga, Bapak Sarino, dalam paparannya menjelaskan bahwa alokasi anggaran tahun 2026 akan difokuskan pada dua prioritas utama: infrastruktur pertanian dan penanganan stunting. \"Sesuai hasil Musrenbangdes sebelumnya, aspirasi terbesar warga adalah perbaikan dan peningkatan jalan usaha tani. Oleh karena itu, 35% dari alokasi dana infrastruktur akan kita gunakan untuk pengerasan jalan tani di Blok C tembus ke Blok D,\" jelasnya.</p><p>Selain itu, program penanganan stunting juga mendapat porsi anggaran yang signifikan. \"Kita tidak main-main dengan stunting. Anggaran dialokasikan untuk Pemberian Makanan Tambahan (PMT) bergizi tinggi bagi balita dan ibu hamil, serta insentif bagi kader Posyandu,\" tambah Pak Sarino.</p><p>Ketua BPD Karang Bunga, Bapak H. Mursyid, menyatakan bahwa BPD telah menyetujui rancangan tersebut setelah melalui beberapa penyesuaian. \"Kami di BPD telah menjalankan fungsi pengawasan dan penganggaran. Kami pastikan setiap rupiah yang dialokasikan benar-benar untuk kebutuhan prioritas warga. Kami akan kawal pelaksanaannya,\" tegasnya.</p>', '01K9VY31NPFFB3581WB53JE75B.jpeg', 'not_featured', 1, 4, 'sah-apbdes-karang-bunga-2026-ditetapkan-sebesar-rp-19-miliar-fokus-pada-jalan-usaha-tani-dan-stunting', NULL, '2025-11-12 03:44:20', '2025-11-12 03:44:20'),
(20, '\'Karang Bunga Digital\' Resmi Diluncurkan, Urus Surat Pengantar Cukup 15 Menit dari Rumah', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Pemerintah Desa Karang Bunga secara resmi meluncurkan Sistem Informasi Desa (SID) terpadu dengan nama <strong>\"Karang Bunga Digital\"</strong>. Peluncuran sistem berbasis website dan aplikasi seluler ini bertujuan untuk memangkas birokrasi, meningkatkan transparansi, dan mempercepat pelayanan administrasi kepada warga.</p><p>Acara peluncuran yang digelar sederhana di Balai Desa ini dihadiri oleh Camat Mandastana. Dalam demonstrasinya, Kaur Perencanaan, Saudara Ardi, menunjukkan bahwa warga kini tidak perlu lagi bolak-balik ke kantor desa untuk mengurus surat-surat umum. \"Cukup buka website atau aplikasi, login dengan NIK, pilih jenis surat, misalnya Surat Keterangan Tidak Mampu (SKTM) atau Surat Pengantar, isi data, lalu ajukan. Dalam waktu maksimal 15 menit, jika Kades ada di tempat, surat sudah bisa diambil atau bahkan dicetak mandiri di rumah,\" papar Ardi.</p><p>Sistem ini tidak hanya melayani surat-menyurat. \"Karang Bunga Digital\" juga menjadi pusat data desa, menampilkan profil desa, data kependudukan (yang terintegrasi secara terbatas), laporan keuangan APBDes secara <em>real-time</em>, serta etalase untuk produk-produk BUMDes dan UMKM lokal.</p><p>Kepala Desa Sarino menyebut ini sebagai lompatan besar. \"Ini adalah wujud komitmen kami pada pemerintahan yang bersih dan cepat. Tidak ada lagi alasan pelayanan lambat. Warga bisa mengawasi anggaran desa langsung dari HP mereka,\" ujarnya.</p><p>Bapak Rohman, salah seorang warga Blok A yang mencoba sistem ini, mengaku sangat terbantu. \"Luar biasa. Tadi saya coba ajukan surat pengantar untuk BPJS, tidak sampai 10 menit sudah ada notifikasi WhatsApp bahwa surat selesai dan bisa di-download. Ini sangat memudahkan kami yang bekerja sebagai petani,\" katanya.</p>', '01K9VY6PVHYNHEBHGRYE5YBH0J.jpg', 'not_featured', 1, 3, 'karang-bunga-digital-resmi-diluncurkan-urus-surat-pengantar-cukup-15-menit-dari-rumah', NULL, '2025-11-12 03:46:20', '2025-11-12 03:46:20'),
(21, 'Sinergi Tiga Pilar: Pemdes, Babinsa, dan Bhabinkamtibmas Giatkan Kembali Siskamling di Seluruh RT', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Menanggapi adanya laporan keresahan warga terkait keamanan, Tiga Pilar Desa Karang Bunga—Pemerintah Desa, Babinsa, dan Bhabinkamtibmas—menggelar Rapat Koordinasi Keamanan dan Ketertiban Masyarakat (Rakor Kamtibmas) di Balai Desa. Hasil utamanya adalah kesepakatan untuk menggalakkan kembali sistem keamanan lingkungan (Siskamling) di seluruh 12 RT.</p><p>Langkah ini diambil setelah adanya beberapa laporan warga di Blok B dan C yang mengaku kehilangan hasil kebun seperti jeruk dan gabah di malam hari, serta adanya orang asing yang mencurigakan.</p><p>Bhabinkamtibmas Desa Karang Bunga, Bripka Iwan Setiawan, menekankan pentingnya pencegahan. \"Keamanan adalah tanggung jawab kita bersama. Polisi tidak bisa bekerja sendiri. Siskamling adalah garda terdepan pencegahan kejahatan di lingkungan kita. Mari kita aktifkan kembali pos ronda,\" ajaknya.</p><p>Senada dengan itu, Babinsa Serda Eko Yulianto menambahkan bahwa pihaknya bersama Bhabinkamtibmas akan melakukan patroli gabungan secara rutin untuk mendukung pos ronda yang aktif. \"Kami akan keliling menyambangi pos-pos ronda untuk memberi semangat dan memastikan situasi aman,\" ujar Serda Eko.</p><p>Pemerintah Desa, dalam hal ini, akan memberikan dukungan penuh. Kepala Desa Sarino mengumumkan bahwa Pemdes akan mengalokasikan dana operasional dari APBDes Perubahan untuk Siskamling. \"Kami akan bantu pengadaan senter, pentungan, dan konsumsi ringan seperti kopi dan gula untuk setiap pos ronda yang aktif. Yang terpenting, warga kembali peduli dengan keamanan tetangganya,\" pungkasnya.</p>', '01K9W2BK7CZE1RK7DNWNH9TRXV.jpeg', 'not_featured', 1, 1, 'sinergi-tiga-pilar-pemdes-babinsa-dan-bhabinkamtibmas-giatkan-kembali-siskamling-di-seluruh-rt', NULL, '2025-11-12 04:58:54', '2025-11-12 04:58:54'),
(22, 'Kinerja BUMDes Gemilang, Desa Karang Bunga Sabet Penghargaan \'Desa Inovatif\' Tingkat Kabupaten', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Prestasi membanggakan kembali diraih oleh Desa Karang Bunga. Dalam acara Penganugerahan Desa Terbaik yang digelar oleh Pemerintah Kabupaten Barito Kuala, Desa Karang Bunga berhasil menyabet penghargaan sebagai <strong>\"Desa Inovatif Kategori Pengembangan Ekonomi Lokal\"</strong> Tahun 2025.</p><p>Penghargaan ini diserahkan langsung oleh Pj. Bupati Barito Kuala kepada Kepala Desa Sarino di Aula Selidah Marabahan, Selasa (4/11). Kemenangan ini tidak lepas dari kinerja gemilang BUMDes \'Karang Bunga Sejahtera\' yang dinilai paling progresif di Batola.</p><p>Tim penilai dari kabupaten menyoroti dua inovasi utama BUMDes Karang Bunga. Pertama, keberhasilannya mengembangkan unit usaha agrowisata petik jeruk siam dan wisata susur sungai. Kedua, kemampuannya mengelola limbah pertanian (serutan kayu) menjadi media tanam jamur tiram yang bernilai ekonomis tinggi, yang kini memberdayakan puluhan ibu rumah tangga.</p><p>\"BUMDes Karang Bunga tidak hanya fokus mencari untung, tetapi berhasil menciptakan <em>multiplier effect</em>. Mereka membuka lapangan kerja, memberdayakan perempuan, dan menciptakan <em>branding</em> baru bagi desa mereka,\" ujar Kepala Dinas PMD Batola dalam sambutannya.</p><p>Kepala Desa Sarino mendedikasikan penghargaan ini untuk seluruh warga. \"Ini adalah hasil kerja keras kita semua, terutama para pengurus BUMDes, KWT, dan Pokdarwis. Penghargaan ini adalah bonus, tapi yang terpenting adalah kesejahteraan warga yang mulai meningkat. Ini akan menjadi cambuk bagi kami untuk terus berinovasi,\" katanya saat diwawancarai setelah menerima piala.</p>', '01K9W2E4SWZNGTMHDCT54BRG42.jpeg', 'not_featured', 1, 2, 'kinerja-bumdes-gemilang-desa-karang-bunga-sabet-penghargaan-desa-inovatif-tingkat-kabupaten', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:00:18', '2025-11-12 05:00:18'),
(23, 'Perdes No. 4 Tahun 2025 Disahkan: Desa Karang Bunga Resmi Miliki Aturan Larangan Buang Sampah di Sungai', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Setelah melalui pembahasan panjang antara Pemerintah Desa dan BPD, Peraturan Desa (Perdes) Nomor 4 Tahun 2025 tentang Pengelolaan Sampah dan Kebersihan Lingkungan akhirnya disahkan. Perdes ini menjadi payung hukum baru bagi desa untuk menindak tegas oknum yang masih membuang sampah sembarangan, terutama ke Sungai Barito.</p><p>Pengesahan Perdes ini dilakukan dalam Sidang Paripurna BPD yang digelar di Balai Desa, Sabtu (1/11). Salah satu pasal yang paling krusial dalam Perdes ini adalah Pasal 12, yang secara eksplisit melarang setiap warga membuang sampah domestik, limbah pertanian, atau bangkai ternak ke badan sungai, drainase, dan fasilitas umum.</p><p>Ketua BPD, H. Mursyid, menjelaskan bahwa Perdes ini bersifat mendesak. \"Karang Bunga dilintasi oleh sungai. Selama ini kita prihatin melihat tumpukan sampah di bantaran. Kita tidak punya payung hukum untuk menindak. Sekarang, dengan Perdes ini, kita punya wewenang,\" jelasnya.</p><p>Perdes ini tidak hanya mengatur larangan, tetapi juga kewajiban. Warga kini diwajibkan untuk memilah sampah dari rumah dan menyetorkannya ke Bank Sampah \'Karang Bersih\'. Bagi yang melanggar larangan buang sampah ke sungai, akan dikenakan sanksi bertahap.</p><p>\"Sanksinya jelas. Pertama teguran lisan oleh Ketua RT. Kedua, teguran tertulis dari Kepala Desa. Jika masih mengulangi, akan ada sanksi denda administrasi sebesar Rp 100.000 yang akan masuk ke kas desa,\" rinci Kades Sarino. \"Ini bukan soal uangnya, ini soal efek jera dan edukasi. Kami akan sosialisasikan Perdes ini ke setiap RT dalam sebulan ke depan.\"</p>', '01K9W2GS8BYRE9K1Z1FMBJHJ8J.jpeg', 'not_featured', 1, 2, 'perdes-no-4-tahun-2025-disahkan-desa-karang-bunga-resmi-miliki-aturan-larangan-buang-sampah-di-sungai', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:01:44', '2025-11-12 05:01:44'),
(24, 'Jalan Usaha Tani Blok C Tembus Blok D Selesai 100%, Petani Jeruk Siap Tingkatkan Hasil Panen', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Kabar gembira bagi para petani di Desa Karang Bunga. Proyek pembangunan dan pengerasan Jalan Usaha Tani (JUT) yang menghubungkan area perkebunan di Blok C dengan Blok D kini telah rampung 100%. Proyek yang didanai sepenuhnya dari Dana Desa (DD) Tahap II Tahun 2025 ini selesai tepat waktu setelah dikerjakan secara swakelola selama 60 hari.</p><p>Jalan sepanjang 800 meter dengan lebar 3 meter ini sebelumnya hanya berupa jalan tanah yang becek dan sulit dilalui saat musim hujan. Kini, dengan konstruksi cor beton, JUT tersebut siap menopang aktivitas pertanian warga sepanjang tahun.</p><p>Kepala Desa Karang Bunga, Bapak Sarino, saat meninjau lokasi, menyatakan kepuasannya. \"Ini adalah jawaban atas aspirasi prioritas warga dalam Musrenbangdes lalu. Jalan ini adalah urat nadi perekonomian pertanian kita. Dulu petani kita susah payah mengangkut jeruk siam pakai gerobak yang terperosok, biayanya jadi mahal,\" ujarnya.</p><p>Dengan selesainya jalan ini, biaya operasional petani untuk mengangkut hasil panen dari kebun ke jalan utama diperkirakan akan turun drastis. \"Luar biasa senangnya. Kalau dulu kami harus bayar upah angkut Rp 15.000 per keranjang, sekarang motor Tossa bisa langsung masuk kebun. Bisa hemat lebih dari setengahnya,\" ungkap Pak Kholis, salah seorang petani jeruk di Blok C.</p><p>Pemerintah Desa berharap, infrastruktur baru ini tidak hanya memperlancar transportasi, tetapi juga memotivasi petani untuk lebih giat merawat kebun mereka dan meningkatkan kualitas serta kuantitas hasil panen jeruk siam yang menjadi ikon Karang Bunga.</p>', '01K9W39A5548C041EMK7KJAFE3.jpeg', 'not_featured', 3, 6, 'jalan-usaha-tani-blok-c-tembus-blok-d-selesai-100-petani-jeruk-siap-tingkatkan-hasil-panen', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:15:08', '2025-11-12 05:15:08'),
(25, 'Pasar Desa \'Karang Bunga Mandiri\' Diresmikan, Puluhan UMKM Lokal Siap Naik Kelas', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Desa Karang Bunga kini memiliki pusat ekonomi baru. Pasar Desa \'Karang Bunga Mandiri\' secara resmi dibuka dan diresmikan oleh Camat Mandastana pada Senin (10/11) pagi. Pembangunan pasar yang menelan biaya dari Alokasi Dana Desa (ADD) dan Bantuan Keuangan Provinsi ini diharapkan dapat menjadi sentra perputaran ekonomi warga.</p><p>Pasar baru ini terdiri dari 20 kios (los) permanen dan 30 lapak terbuka. Desainnya semi-modern namun tetap mengedepankan sirkulasi udara yang baik. Fasilitas penunjang seperti toilet umum yang bersih, mushola, dan area parkir yang memadai juga telah disiapkan.</p><p>Dalam sambutannya, Kepala Desa Sarino menjelaskan bahwa pasar ini akan dikelola sepenuhnya oleh BUMDes \'Karang Bunga Sejahtera\'. \"Prioritas pengisi kios adalah UMKM dan pedagang lokal Karang Bunga. Kita punya penjual olahan ikan patin, pengrajin kue basah, dan tentu saja lapak khusus untuk hasil bumi seperti jeruk siam dan sayuran,\" katanya.</p><p>Pasar ini dibangun untuk menggantikan pasar kaget mingguan yang sebelumnya beroperasi di pinggir jalan utama dan sering menimbulkan kemacetan. \"Dengan adanya pasar ini, kami pedagang kecil merasa lebih dihargai. Tempatnya bersih, teduh, dan tidak kehujanan. Pembeli pasti lebih nyaman,\" tutur Ibu Zaleha, seorang penjual kue basah yang kini menempati salah satu kios.</p><p>Camat Mandastana dalam peresmiannya berharap Pasar Desa ini tidak hanya menjadi tempat jual beli, tapi juga pusat interaksi sosial dan promosi produk unggulan desa.</p>', '01K9W3FAGZCJGK5JF8FPR91KMD.jpeg', 'not_featured', 3, 5, 'pasar-desa-karang-bunga-mandiri-diresmikan-puluhan-umkm-lokal-siap-naik-kelas', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:18:25', '2025-11-12 05:18:25'),
(26, 'Krisis Air Bersih Berakhir: Program Pamsimas III di RT 10 dan 11 Resmi Mengalir', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Senyum bahagia terpancar dari wajah warga RT 10 dan RT 11 di Blok D, Desa Karang Bunga. Penantian mereka akan air bersih yang layak konsumsi akhirnya berakhir. Program Penyediaan Air Minum dan Sanitasi Berbasis Masyarakat (Pamsimas) III secara resmi dioperasikan dan air bersih kini telah mengalir ke 150 Sambungan Rumah (SR) baru di dua RT tersebut.</p><p>Sebelumnya, warga di area ini, yang merupakan wilayah terjauh dari pusat desa, masih mengandalkan air sumur gali yang keruh dan berbau gambut, serta air Sungai Barito untuk kebutuhan MCK.</p><p>\"Alhamdulillah, sekarang kami tidak perlu lagi repot-repot menyaring air atau beli air galon untuk masak. Airnya jernih, tidak berbau, dan mengalir 24 jam. Rasanya seperti mimpi,\" ujar Ibu Maimunah, warga RT 11, sambil menunjukkan meteran air di depan rumahnya.</p><p>Program Pamsimas ini merupakan hasil kolaborasi antara dana pemerintah pusat dan swadaya masyarakat. Warga secara gotong royong melakukan penggalian pipa, sementara pemerintah desa memfasilitasi pembangunan menara air (reservoir) dan instalasi pengolahan air sederhana (WTP Mini).</p><p>Koordinator Kelompok Keswadayaan Masyarakat (KKM) Pamsimas Karang Bunga menjelaskan bahwa iuran bulanan akan dikelola secara transparan untuk biaya operasional dan perawatan. \"Ini milik kita bersama, jadi harus kita jaga bersama. Dengan air bersih ini, kami berharap kesehatan warga, terutama anak-anak, akan semakin meningkat,\" tutupnya.</p>', '01K9W3HYA17SA2T98EF740R7QJ.jpeg', 'not_featured', 3, 1, 'krisis-air-bersih-berakhir-program-pamsimas-iii-di-rt-10-dan-11-resmi-mengalir', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:19:51', '2025-11-12 05:19:51'),
(27, 'Wajah Baru Balai Desa Karang Bunga: Representatif, Ramah Disabilitas, dan Siap Beri Pelayanan Prima', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Setelah melalui proses renovasi total selama empat bulan, Balai Desa Karang Bunga akhirnya kembali dibuka untuk pelayanan publik dengan wajah yang benar-benar baru. Proyek renovasi yang menggunakan anggaran Bantuan Keuangan (Bankeu) Provinsi ini berhasil mengubah bangunan lama menjadi lebih modern, representatif, dan fungsional.</p><p>Perubahan paling mencolok terlihat pada ruang pelayanan publik. Jika sebelumnya sempit dan pengap, kini ruang tunggu didesain terbuka, luas, dan dilengkapi kursi tunggu yang nyaman. Meja pelayanan dibuat terpusat (sistem satu meja) untuk memudahkan warga mengurus administrasi.</p><p>Kepala Desa Sarino menjelaskan bahwa renovasi ini bukan sekadar untuk gagah-gagahan. \"Yang utama adalah kenyamanan warga dan semangat baru bagi aparat desa. Kantor yang baik harus menghasilkan pelayanan yang baik pula,\" katanya.</p><p>Inovasi penting lainnya adalah penambahan fasilitas ramah disabilitas. Kini Balai Desa dilengkapi dengan <em>ramp</em> (jalur landai) di pintu masuk dan toilet khusus yang bisa diakses oleh pengguna kursi roda. \"Kami ingin semua warga, tanpa terkecuali, merasa nyaman saat datang ke kantor desa,\" tambah Kasi Pelayanan.</p><p>Dengan selesainya renovasi ini, seluruh pelayanan administrasi yang sebelumnya sempat dipindahkan sementara, kini telah kembali normal di Balai Desa. Warga pun menyambut baik perubahan ini, merasa lebih \'dihargai\' saat datang ke kantor desa.</p>', '01K9W3MYDWGEJDNK78E96HSG3P.jpeg', 'not_featured', 3, 4, 'wajah-baru-balai-desa-karang-bunga-representatif-ramah-disabilitas-dan-siap-beri-pelayanan-prima', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:21:29', '2025-11-12 05:21:29'),
(28, 'Tingkatkan Prestasi Olahraga, Drainase dan Rumput Lapangan Sepak Bola \'Tunas Harapan\' Selesai Direvitalisasi', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Para pemuda dan pecinta olahraga di Desa Karang Bunga kini bisa tersenyum lebar. Proyek revitalisasi Lapangan Sepak Bola \'Tunas Harapan\' yang menjadi kebanggaan desa telah selesai dikerjakan. Fokus utama pembangunan yang didanai dari Dana Desa bidang Kepemudaan ini adalah perbaikan sistem drainase dan penanaman rumput baru.</p><p>Selama bertahun-tahun, lapangan ini selalu menjadi \'kubangan\' setiap kali hujan deras, sehingga tidak bisa dipakai. Hal ini menghambat pembinaan bibit-bibit pesepakbola desa. \"Dulu kalau hujan sedikit saja, main bola sudah seperti main di sawah,\" keluh Rian, kapten tim sepak bola Karang Taruna.</p><p>Tim Pelaksana Kegiatan (TPK) Desa Karang Bunga bekerja selama dua bulan untuk membangun sistem drainase baru di sekeliling lapangan dan di bawah permukaan lapangan. Setelah itu, permukaan lapangan diratakan dan ditanami rumput jenis <em>zoysia matrella</em> yang dikenal kuat dan berkualitas.</p><p>\"Sekarang lapangannya sudah standar kabupaten. Tidak becek lagi walau habis hujan. Kami jadi lebih semangat latihan untuk persiapan turnamen antar-desa (Tarkam) tahun depan,\" ujar Rian dengan antusias.</p><p>Kepala Desa berharap, dengan fasilitas yang kini jauh lebih baik, prestasi olahraga desa, khususnya sepak bola dan voli (yang lapangannya berada di kompleks yang sama), dapat semakin meningkat dan mengharumkan nama Desa Karang Bunga di tingkat kecamatan maupun kabupaten.</p>', '01K9W3QT28V7BYQX46D66KFNNC.jpeg', 'not_featured', 3, 3, 'tingkatkan-prestasi-olahraga-drainase-dan-rumput-lapangan-sepak-bola-tunas-harapan-selesai-direvitalisasi', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:23:03', '2025-11-12 05:23:03'),
(29, 'Antisipasi Serangan CVPD, Ratusan Petani Jeruk Siam Karang Bunga Ikuti Sekolah Lapang dari Dinas Pertanian', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Penyakit <em>Citrus Vein Phloem Degeneration</em> (CVPD) masih menjadi ancaman utama bagi produktivitas jeruk siam, komoditas unggulan Desa Karang Bunga. Untuk mengantisipasi kerugian panen yang lebih besar, Dinas Pertanian (Distan) Kabupaten Barito Kuala menggelar program Sekolah Lapang Pengendalian Hama Terpadu (SLPHT) yang difokuskan pada penanganan CVPD.</p><p>Acara yang dipusatkan di lahan percontohan Blok A ini diikuti oleh lebih dari 100 petani yang tergabung dalam berbagai kelompok tani. Selama tiga hari, mereka mendapatkan materi langsung di kebun, bukan hanya di dalam kelas. Materi mencakup deteksi dini gejala CVPD, cara mengidentifikasi kutu loncat (Diaphorina citri) sebagai vektor penyakit, dan teknik pengendalian yang ramah lingkungan.</p><p>Bapak Udin, salah seorang petani jeruk, mengaku sangat terbantu. \"Selama ini kalau daun sudah kuning (gejala CVPD), kami pasrah saja dan langsung ditebang. Ternyata tadi diajarkan cara pencegahannya, yaitu dengan sanitasi kebun yang benar dan pelepasan musuh alami,\" ujarnya.</p><p>Petugas Penyuluh Lapangan (PPL) Kecamatan Mandastana, yang bertindak sebagai fasilitator, menjelaskan bahwa program ini menekankan pada pencegahan. \"CVPD itu seperti kanker pada jeruk, sulit disembuhkan jika sudah parah. Kuncinya ada di pencegahan. Kami mengajarkan petani untuk rutin melakukan <em>monitoring</em> kebun dan segera melakukan <em>eradikasi</em> (pemusnahan) selektif pada pohon yang baru terinfeksi agar tidak menular,\" jelasnya.</p><p>Program ini diakhiri dengan penyerahan bantuan bibit jeruk siam berlabel bebas penyakit dan agens hayati (musuh alami hama) kepada para peserta.</p>', '01K9W43BYB1B1RJS2MYHR8140R.jpeg', 'not_featured', 4, 2, 'antisipasi-serangan-cvpd-ratusan-petani-jeruk-siam-karang-bunga-ikuti-sekolah-lapang-dari-dinas-pertanian', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:29:22', '2025-11-12 05:29:22');
INSERT INTO `article_news` (`id`, `name`, `content`, `thumbnail`, `is_featured`, `category_id`, `author_id`, `slug`, `deleted_at`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(30, 'Sambut Musim Tanam Gadu, Kelompok Tani \'Maju Bersama\' Terapkan Sistem Tanam Jajar Legowo 2:1', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Memasuki musim tanam Gadu (musim tanam kedua), para petani yang tergabung dalam Kelompok Tani (Poktan) \'Maju Bersama\' di Blok D Desa Karang Bunga tidak lagi menggunakan metode tanam acak. Tahun ini, mereka secara serentak beralih ke sistem tanam <strong>Jajar Legowo 2:1</strong>, sebuah teknik yang dianjurkan oleh Kementerian Pertanian untuk meningkatkan produksi padi.</p><p>Sistem Jajar Legowo adalah cara tanam padi di mana setiap dua baris tanaman diselingi oleh satu baris kosong yang lebih lebar. Ini bukan lahan kosong yang terbuang, melainkan \"lorong\" yang memiliki banyak fungsi.</p><p>Bapak Kholis, Ketua Poktan \'Maju Bersama\', menjelaskan antusiasme anggotanya. \"Kami sudah lihat demonstasi plot (demplot) dari PPL tahun lalu. Dengan sistem ini, semua tanaman jadi tanaman pinggir, dapat sinar matahari penuh. Hama tikus juga tidak suka karena sawahnya terlalu terbuka,\" katanya saat ditemui di sela-sela kegiatan tanam bersama.</p><p>Selain itu, lanjutnya, sistem ini sangat memudahkan perawatan. \"Waktu menyemprot hama atau memberi pupuk susulan, kami bisa lewat \'lorong\' itu. Tidak ada lagi tanaman yang terinjak-injak,\" tambahnya.</p><p>Pemerintah Desa Karang Bunga sangat mendukung inisiatif ini dengan memberikan bantuan pinjam pakai alat tanam (transplanter) untuk mempercepat proses tanam. Diharapkan, dengan penerapan Jajar Legowo, produksi gabah kering panen (GKP) di Karang Bunga yang rata-rata 5 ton per hektar, bisa meningkat menjadi 6 hingga 6,5 ton per hektar pada musim panen mendatang.</p>', '01K9W47PPCTX39VHCXV79CR0N1.jpeg', 'not_featured', 4, 3, 'sambut-musim-tanam-gadu-kelompok-tani-maju-bersama-terapkan-sistem-tanam-jajar-legowo-21', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:31:44', '2025-11-12 05:31:44'),
(31, 'Manfaatkan Potensi Sungai Barito, Pokdakan \'Barito Jaya\' Sukses Panen Raya 2 Ton Ikan Patin', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Kelompok Pembudidaya Ikan (Pokdakan) \'Barito Jaya\' Desa Karang Bunga membuktikan bahwa potensi Sungai Barito bukan hanya untuk transportasi. Bertempat di bantaran sungai Blok A, kelompok ini sukses menggelar panen raya perdana ikan patin (Pangasius) dari keramba jaring apung (KJA) mereka. Tak tanggung-tanggung, 2 ton ikan patin segar berhasil diangkat dari 10 petak keramba.</p><p>Keberhasilan ini merupakan buah dari program diversifikasi usaha tani yang didukung oleh Dinas Perikanan Kabupaten Batola. Dua tahun lalu, para anggota Pokdakan yang sebagian besar adalah petani jeruk, mendapat bantuan bibit dan pelatihan pembuatan KJA.</p><p>Bapak Hermansyah, Ketua Pokdakan, menceritakan tantangannya. \"Awalnya kami ragu, karena takut kerambanya hanyut atau ikan dicuri. Tantangan terbesar ternyata adalah harga pakan pabrikan yang sangat mahal,\" ujarnya.</p><p>Namun, kelompok ini tidak menyerah. Dengan bimbingan penyuluh perikanan, mereka berhasil membuat pakan ikan alternatif (pakan mandiri) berbahan baku lokal, seperti dedak, olahan ikan rucah, dan vitamin. \"Dengan pakan mandiri, kami bisa menekan biaya produksi hingga 40%. Hasilnya, ikan patin kami bisa tumbuh optimal dengan bobot rata-rata 1 kg per ekor dalam 8 bulan,\" jelasnya bangga.</p><p>Seluruh hasil panen raya ini sudah ditunggu oleh para tengkulak dari Banjarmasin dan Marabahan. Kesuksesan Pokdakan \'Barito Jaya\' diharapkan dapat menular ke kelompok lain untuk memanfaatkan potensi perairan Sungai Barito secara berkelanjutan.</p>', '01K9W4BCTFN0X5E7Y391DW39CS.jpeg', 'not_featured', 4, 4, 'manfaatkan-potensi-sungai-barito-pokdakan-barito-jaya-sukses-panen-raya-2-ton-ikan-patin', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:33:45', '2025-11-12 05:33:45'),
(32, 'Inovasi KWT Mawar: Sulap Jeruk Siam Afkir Jadi \'Dodol Jeruk\' dan \'Sirup Siam\' Bernilai Ekonomi Tinggi', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Jika musim panen raya tiba, selalu ada jeruk siam yang \'afkir\' atau tidak lolos sortir untuk dijual sebagai buah segar karena ukurannya terlalu kecil atau kulitnya kurang mulus. Dulu, jeruk afkir ini hanya dibiarkan membusuk atau dijual sangat murah. Namun, di tangan ibu-ibu kreatif Kelompok Wanita Tani (KWT) Mawar, limbah panen itu kini menjelma menjadi produk olahan bernilai jual tinggi.</p><p>Bertempat di rumah produksi sederhana mereka, KWT Mawar kini rutin memproduksi <strong>\"Dodol Jeruk Siam\"</strong> dan <strong>\"Sirup Jeruk Siam Karang Bunga\"</strong>. Inovasi ini berawal dari pelatihan pascapanen yang difasilitasi oleh Tim Penggerak PKK Desa Karang Bunga.</p><p>\"Sayang sekali melihat jeruk yang sebenarnya manis tapi terbuang. Kami coba-coba resep, akhirnya kami temukan formula dodol yang legit dengan rasa asam-manis jeruk yang khas,\" ungkap Ibu Halimah, Ketua KWT Mawar.</p><p>Prosesnya pun masih tradisional namun higienis. Kulit jeruk dimanfaatkan untuk diambil sarinya, sementara bulir jeruknya diolah menjadi dodol. Produk mereka kini telah mengantongi izin Pangan Industri Rumah Tangga (PIRT) dan sertifikasi Halal.</p><p>Produk olahan ini tidak hanya laku di pasar desa, tetapi juga sudah mulai dipasarkan ke toko-toko oleh-oleh di Banjarmasin berkat bantuan promosi dari BUMDes. \"Sekarang, petani malah sengaja menyisihkan jeruk afkirnya untuk kami beli. Ini jadi tambahan pendapatan yang lumayan bagi ibu-ibu di sini,\" tutupnya sambil tersenyum.</p>', '01K9W4DMEEEVFAZVRPGWHSP9F2.jpeg', 'not_featured', 4, 1, 'inovasi-kwt-mawar-sulap-jeruk-siam-afkir-jadi-dodol-jeruk-dan-sirup-siam-bernilai-ekonomi-tinggi', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:34:58', '2025-11-12 05:34:58'),
(33, 'Modernisasi Pertanian: Gapoktan Karang Bunga Resmi Operasikan Combine Harvester Bantuan Kementan', '<p><strong>KARANG BUNGA, Barito Kuala</strong> – Era panen padi manual menggunakan sabit di Desa Karang Bunga perlahan mulai tergantikan. Gabungan Kelompok Tani (Gapoktan) Karang Bunga Jaya secara resmi menerima dan mengoperasikan satu unit alat mesin pertanian (Alsintan) canggih berupa <em>Combine Harvester</em> (mesin pemanen padi). Bantuan ini merupakan bagian dari program modernisasi pertanian dari Kementerian Pertanian yang disalurkan melalui Dinas Pertanian Batola.</p><p>Mesin pemanen raksasa berwarna merah itu langsung diuji coba di lahan sawah milik Gapoktan yang sedang memasuki masa panen raya. Dalam sekejap, puluhan warga yang menonton dibuat takjub. Mesin ini mampu melakukan tiga pekerjaan sekaligus: memotong, merontokkan, dan membersihkan gabah.</p><p>Bapak H. Mursyid, Ketua Gapoktan,menyatakan rasa syukurnya. \"Ini seperti mimpi bagi kami. Dulu, untuk memanen satu hektar sawah, kami butuh 10-15 orang pekerja dan waktu 2 hari. Sekarang dengan mesin ini, 3 jam saja selesai dan gabah langsung masuk karung,\" jelasnya.</p><p>Menurutnya, penggunaan <em>combine harvester</em> ini akan menekan biaya panen secara drastis dan mengurangi kehilangan gabah (losses) saat proses panen yang biasanya mencapai 10% jika dilakukan manual.</p><p>Alsintan ini akan dikelola oleh Unit Pelayanan Jasa Alsintan (UPJA) di bawah naungan BUMDes. Petani yang ingin menggunakan jasanya bisa mendaftar dengan biaya sewa yang jauh lebih murah dibanding upah tenaga kerja manual. \"Kami berharap dengan alat ini, anak-anak muda desa tidak malu lagi jadi petani karena sekarang kita sudah modern,\" pungkas H. Mursyid.</p>', '01K9W4FM549NBQHSYPAGP2FY9W.jpeg', 'not_featured', 4, 5, 'modernisasi-pertanian-gapoktan-karang-bunga-resmi-operasikan-combine-harvester-bantuan-kementan', NULL, '2025-11-12 05:36:03', '2025-11-12 05:36:03');

